  <Name>k__BackingField: Isaiah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: isa
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: SuperscriptionRebellious Judah'
      title: SuperscriptionRebellious Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'The vision of Isaiah son of Amoz, which he saw concerning Judah and
        Jerusalem in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Hear, heavens, and listen, earth, for Yahweh has spoken: \u201CI
        reared children and I brought them up, but they rebelled against me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'An ox knows its owner and a donkey the manger of its master. Israel
        does not know; my people do not understand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ah, sinful nation, a people heavy with iniquity, offspring of evildoers,
        children who deal corruptly. They have forsaken Yahweh; they have despised
        the holy one of Israel. They are estranged and gone backward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why do you want to be beaten again? You continue in rebellion. The
        whole of the head is sick, and the whole of the heart is faint. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'From the sole of the foot and up to the head there is no health in
        it; bruise and sore and bleeding wound have not been cleansed, and they have
        not been bound up and not softened with the oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Your country is desolate, your cities are burned with fire; As for
        your land, aliens are devouring it in your presence, and it is desolate,
        like devastation by foreigners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the daughter of Zion is left like a booth in a vineyard, like
        a shelter in a cucumber field, like a city that is besieged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If Yahweh of hosts had not left us survivors,  we would have been
        as few as Sodom, we would have become like Gomorrah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hear the word of Yahweh, rulers of Sodom! Listen to the teaching
        of our God, people of Gomorrah! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'What is the abundance of your sacrifices to me? says Yahweh. I have
        had enough of burnt offerings of rams and the fat of fattened animals and
        I do not delight in the blood of bulls and ram-lambs and goats. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When you come to appear before me, who asked for this from your hand:
        you trampling my courts? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You must not continue to bring offerings of futility, incense\u2014it
        is an abomination to me; new moon and Sabbath, the calling of a convocation\u2014
        I cannot endure iniquity with solemn assembly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your new moons and your appointed festivals my soul hates; they have
        become to me like a burden, I am not able to bear them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And when you stretch out your hands, I will hide my eyes from you;
        even though you make many prayers,  I will not be listening. Your hands are
        full of blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Wash! Make yourselves clean! Remove the evil of your doings from
        before my eyes! Cease to do evil! '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Learn to do good! Seek justice! Rescue the oppressed! Defend the
        orphan! Plead for the widow! '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CCome now, and let us argue,\u201D says Yahweh. \u201CEven though
        your sins are like scarlet, they will be white like snow; even though they
        are red like crimson, they shall become like wool. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If you are willing and you are obedient, you shall eat the good of
        the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Purifying Jerusalem'
      title: Purifying Jerusalem
      number: 20
      content: "But if you refuse and you rebel, you shall be devoured by the sword.
        For the mouth of Yahweh has spoken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'How has a faithful city become like a whore? Full of justice, righteousness
        lodged in her, but now murderers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Your silver has become as dross; Your wine is diluted with waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Your princes are rebels and companions of thieves. Every one loves
        a bribe and runs after gifts. They do not defend the orphan and the legal
        dispute of the widow does not come before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore, the declaration of the Lord Yahweh of hosts, the Mighty
        One of Israel: \u201CAh, I will be relieved of my enemies, and I will avenge
        myself on my foes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And I will turn my hand against you; I will purify your dross like
        lye, and I will remove all of your tin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And I will restore your judges, as at the first, and your counselors,
        as at the beginning. After this you will be called the city of righteousness,
        faithful city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Zion will be redeemed by justice, and those of her who repent, by
        righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But the destruction of rebels and sinners shall be together, and
        those who forsake Yahweh will perish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For you will be ashamed of the oaks in which you delighted, and you
        will be disgraced because of the gardens that you have chosen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For you shall be like an oak withering its leaves, and like a garden
        where there is no water for her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And the strong man shall become like tinder, and his work like a
        spark. And both of them shall burn together, and there is not one to quench
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Mountain of Yahweh'
      title: The Mountain of Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: 'The word that Isaiah son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it shall happen in the future of the days the mountain of the
        house of Yahweh shall be established; it will be among the highest of the
        mountains, and it shall be raised from the hills. All of the nations shall
        travel to him; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "many peoples shall come. And they shall say, \u201CCome, let us go
        up to the mountain of Yahweh, to the house of the God of Jacob, and may he
        teach us part of his ways, and let us walk in his paths.\u201D For instruction
        shall go out from Zion, and the word of Yahweh from Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Day of Yahweh'
      title: The Day of Yahweh
      number: 4
      content: 'He shall judge between the nations and he shall arbitrate for many
        peoples. They shall beat their swords into ploughshares and their spears
        into pruning hooks. A nation shall not lift up a sword against a nation,
        and they shall not learn war again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'House of Jacob, come and let us walk in the light of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For you have forsaken your people, house of Jacob, because they are
        full from the east, and of soothsayers like the Philistines, and they make
        alliances with the offspring of foreigners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And its land is filled with silver and gold, and there is no end
        to its treasures; and its land is filled with horses, and there is no end
        to its chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Its land is filled with idols; they bow down to the work of their
        hands, to what they made with their fingers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So humanity is humbled; everyone is humbled, and you must not forgive
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Enter into the rock and hide yourself in the dust from the presence
        of the terror of Yahweh and from the glory of his majesty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The haughty eyes of humanity will be brought low, and the pride of
        everyone will be humbled, and Yahweh alone will be exalted on that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For there is a day for Yahweh of hosts against all of the proud and
        the lofty and against all that is lifted up and humble,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and against all the lofty and lifted up cedars of Lebanon, and against
        all the large trees of Bashan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and against all the high mountains, and against all the lofty hills, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and against every kind of high tower, and against every kind of fortified
        wall, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and against all the ships of Tarshish, and against all the ships
        of desire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the haughtiness of the people shall be humbled, and the pride
        of everyone shall be brought low, and Yahweh alone will be exalted on that
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the idols shall pass away entirely, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and they will enter into the caves of the rocks and into the holes
        of the ground from the presence of the terror of Yahweh and from the glory
        of his majesty when he rises to terrify the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "On that day humanity will throw away its idols of silver and its
        idols of gold, which they made for it to worship, to the rodents and to the
        bats\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'to enter into the crevices of the rocks and into the clefts of the
        crags from the presence of the terror of Yahweh and from the glory of his
        majesty, when he rises to terrify the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Turn away from humanity, who has breath in its nostrils,  for by
        what is it esteemed? '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Leaders of Judah and Jerusalem'
      title: Leaders of Judah and Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'For look, the Lord Yahweh of hosts is removing every source of support 
        from Jerusalem and from Judah: all of the supplies of bread and all of the
        supplies of water, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'mighty warrior and man of war, judge and prophet, and diviner and
        elder, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'captain of fifty and the honorable men of rank, and counselor and
        skillful magicians and skillful enchanter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And I will make boys their princes, and children shall rule over
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the people will be oppressed by each other  and a man by his
        neighbor. The boy will act arrogantly toward the elder, and the dishonorable
        toward the honorable. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Indeed, a man will seize his brother in the house of his father:
        \u201CYou have a cloak;  you shall be a leader for us, and this heap of ruins
        shall be under your hand!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He will lift up his voice on that day, saying, \u201CI will not be
        a healer; in my house there is no bread and there is no cloak. You shall
        not make me the leader of the people!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For Jerusalem has stumbled, and Judah has fallen because their speech
        and their deeds are against Yahweh, defying the eyes of his glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The look on their faces testifies against them and they declare their
        sin like Sodom; they do not hide it. Woe to their soul! For they have dealt
        out evil to themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Tell the innocent that it is good for they shall eat the fruit of
        their deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Woe to the wicked! It is bad! For what is done by his hands will
        be done to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "My people\u2014children are their oppressors, and women rule over
        them. My people, your leaders are misleading you, and they confuse the course
        of your paths. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yahweh takes his stand to conduct a legal case and takes his stand
        to judge the peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Yahweh enters into judgment with the elders of his people and its
        princes. \u201CAnd you! You have devoured the vineyard; the spoil of the
        poor is in your houses! "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: The Pride of Jerusalem\u2019s Women"
      title: "The Pride of Jerusalem\u2019s Women"
      number: 15
      content: "Why do you crush my people and grind the face of the poor?\u201D
        declares the Lord Yahweh of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Yahweh said: \u201CBecause the daughters of Zion are haughty,
        and they walk with outstretched neck, and they give flirting glances with
        their eyes, mincing along as they go,  and with their feet they rattle their
        bangles,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "the Lord will make the heads of the daughters of Zion scabby, and
        Yahweh will lay their foreheads bare.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In that day the Lord will take away the finery of the anklets and
        the headbands and the crescent necklaces, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the pendants and the bracelets and the veils, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the headdresses and the armlets and the sashes, and the perfume boxes
        and the amulets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the signet rings and the nose rings, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'the festal robes and the mantles, and the cloaks and the handbags, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and the mirrors and the linen garments, and the turbans and the wraps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And this shall happen: There will be a stench instead of perfume,
        and a rope instead of a sash, and baldness instead of a well-set hairdo,
        and a clothing wrap of sackcloth instead of a rich robe, branding instead
        of beauty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Your men shall fall by the sword, and your warriors in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And her gates shall lament and mourn, and she shall be banished;
        she shall sit upon the ground. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Glory of the Branch of Yahweh'
      title: The Glory of the Branch of Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: " And seven women shall grasp at one man on that day, saying, \u201CWe
        will eat our own bread, and we will wear our own clothing; only let us be
        called by your name!  Take away our disgrace!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'On that day the branch of Yahweh shall become beautiful and glorious,
        and the fruit of the land shall become the pride and glory of the survivors
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And this shall happen: He who is left in Zion and he who remains
        in Jerusalem will be called holy, everyone written for life in Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'when the Lord has washed away the filth of the daughters of Zion
        and cleansed the blood of Jerusalem from her midst by a spirit of judgment
        and by a spirit of burning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Yahweh will create over all of the site of Mount Zion  and over
        her assembly a cloud by day and smoke and the brightness of flaming fire
        by night. Indeed, over all the glory there will be a canopy, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and it will be a shelter for shade from the heat by day, and a refuge
        and a hiding place from rainstorm and from rain. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of the Vineyard'
      title: The Song of the Vineyard
      number: 1
      content: 'Let me sing for my beloved a song of my love concerning his vineyard:
        My beloved had a vineyard on a fertile hill.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he dug it and cleared it of stones, and he planted it with choice
        vines,  and he built a watchtower in the middle of it, and he even hewed
        out a wine vat in it, and he waited for it to yield grapes\u2014 but it yielded
        wild grapes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And now, inhabitants of Jerusalem and men of Judah, judge between
        me and my vineyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'What more was there to do for my vineyard that I have not done in
        it? Why did I hope for it to yield grapes, and it yielded wild grapes? '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And now let me tell you what I myself am about to do to my vineyard.
        I will remove its hedge, and it shall become a devastation. I will break
        down its wall, and it shall become a trampling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And I will make it a wasteland; it shall not be pruned and hoed,
        and it shall be overgrown with briers and thornbushes.  And concerning the
        clouds, I will command them not to send rain down upon it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Woes on the Wicked'
      title: Woes on the Wicked
      number: 7
      content: 'For the vineyard of Yahweh of hosts is the house of Israel, and the
        man of Judah is the plantation of his delight. And he waited for justice, 
        but look! Bloodshed!  For righteousness,  but look! A cry of distress!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ah! Those who join house with house, they join field together with
        field until there is no place  and you are caused to dwell alone in the midst
        of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Yahweh of hosts said in my ears: Surely many houses shall become
        a desolation, large and beautiful ones without inhabitant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For ten acres of vineyard shall yield one bath,  and the seed of
        a homer will yield an ephah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ah! Those who rise early in the morning, they pursue strong drink.
        Those who linger in the evening, wine inflames them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And there will be lyre and harp, tambourine and flute, and wine at
        their feasts, but they do not look at the deeds of Yahweh, and they do not
        see the work of his hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore my people will go into exile without knowledge, and their
        nobles will be men of hunger, and their multitude is parched with thirst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore Sheol has enlarged its throat, and it has opened wide its
        mouth without limit, and her nobles will go down, and her multitude, her
        tumult and those who revel in her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And humankind is bowed down, and man is brought low, and the eyes
        of the haughty are humiliated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Yahweh of hosts is exalted by justice, and the holy God shows
        himself holy by righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And then the lambs will graze as in their pasture, and fatlings,
        kids will eat among the sites of ruins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Ah! Those who drag iniquity along with the cords of falsehood and
        sin as with rope of the cart, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "those who say, \u201CLet him make haste; let him hurry his work so
        that we may see it and let it draw near and let the plan of the holy one
        of Israel come so that we may know it!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Ah! Those who call evil good and good evil, those who put darkness
        for light and light for darkness, those who put bitter for sweet and sweet
        for bitter! '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Ah! Those who are wise in their own eyes and have understanding in
        their view!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Ah! Heroes at drinking wine, and men of capability at mixing strong
        drink! '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Those who acquit the guilty because of a bribe and remove the justice
        of the innocent from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Therefore as the tongue of fire devours the stubble, and dry grass
        sinks down in the flame, so their root will become like the stench, and their
        blossom will go up like the dust. For they have rejected the instruction
        of Yahweh of hosts, and they have treated the word of the holy one of Israel
        with contempt. '
      comments: []
    - name: "25: Yahweh\u2019s Outstretched Hand"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Outstretched Hand"
      number: 25
      content: "Therefore Yahweh\u2019s wrath was kindled against his people, and
        he stretched out his hand against them and struck them,  and the mountains
        quaked, and their corpses were like refuse in the middle of the streets.
        In all of this his anger has not turned back, and still his hand is stretched
        out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And he will raise a signal for a nation from afar, and he will whistle
        for it from the end of the earth. And look! It comes quickly, swiftly! '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'None is weary, and none among him stumbles; none slumbers and none
        sleeps. And no loincloth on his waist is opened, and no thong of his sandals
        is drawn away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Whose arrows are sharp, and all of his bows are bent. The hoofs of
        his horses are reckoned like flint, and his wheels like the storm wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'His roaring is like the lion, and he roars like young lions. And
        he growls and seizes his prey, and he carries it off, and not one can rescue
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And he will roar over him on that day like the roaring of the sea,
        and if one looks to the land, look! Darkness! Distress! And the light grows
        dark with its clouds. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Isaiah\u2019s Commission"
      title: "Isaiah\u2019s Commission"
      number: 1
      content: 'In the year of the death of Uzziah the king, I saw the Lord sitting
        on a high and raised throne, and the hem of his robe was filling the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Seraphs were standing above him. Each had six wings: with two he
        covered his face, and with two he covered his feet, and with two he flew. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the one called to the other and said, \u201CHoly, holy, holy
        is Yahweh of hosts! The whole earth is full of his glory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the pivots of the thresholds shook from the sound of those who
        called, and the house was filled with smoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I said, \u201CWoe to me! For I am destroyed! For I am a man of
        unclean lips, and I am living among a people of unclean lips, for my eyes
        have seen the king, Yahweh of hosts!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then one of the seraphs flew to me, and in his hand was a hot coal
        he had taken from the altar with tongs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he touched my mouth, and he said, \u201CLook! This has touched
        your lips and has removed your guilt, and your sin is annulled.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then I heard the voice of the Lord saying, \u201CWhom shall I send?
        And who will go for us?\u201D And I said, \u201CI am here! Send me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said, \u201CGo and say to this people, \u2018Keep on listening
        and do not comprehend! And keep on looking and do not understand!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Make the heart of this people insensitive, and make its ears unresponsive,
        and shut its eyes so that it may not look with its eyes and listen with its
        ears and comprehend with its mind and turn back, and it may be healed for
        him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I said, \u201CUntil when, Lord?\u201D And he said, \u201CUntil
        the cities lie wasted without inhabitant, and houses without people, and
        the land is ruined and a waste, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and Yahweh sends the people far away, and the abandonment is great
        in the midst of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And even if only a tenth part remain, again she will be destroyed 
        like a terebinth or like an oak, which although felled, a tree stump remains
        in them. The seed of holiness will be her tree stump.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sign to Ahaz'
      title: The Sign to Ahaz
      number: 1
      content: 'This happened in the days of Ahaz, son of Jotham, son of Uzziah,
        king of Judah. Rezin, king of Aram, and Pekah, son of Remaliah, king of Israel,
        went up to Jerusalem for warfare against it, but he was not able to fight
        against it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When it was reported to the house of David, saying \u201CAram stands
        by Ephraim,\u201D his heart and the heart of his people shook like the shaking
        of the trees of the forest because of the wind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Yahweh said to Isaiah, \u201CGo out to meet Ahaz, you and Shear-Jashub
        your son, at the end of the conduit of the upper pool on the highway of the
        washer\u2019s field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you must say to him, \u2018Take heed and be quiet! You must not
        fear, and your heart must not be faint because of these two stumps of smoldering
        firebrands, because of the fierce anger of Rezin and Aram and the son of
        Remaliah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Because Aram has plotted evil against you with Ephraim and the son
        of Remaliah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CLet us go up against Judah and let us tear her apart, and let
        us lay it open and so bring it unto ourselves, and let us install the son
        of Tabeel as king in her midst.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Thus says the Lord Yahweh, \u201CIt shall not stand, and it shall
        not come to pass. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the head of Aram is Damascus, and the head of Damascus is Rezin,
        and in sixty-five years from now Ephraim will be too shattered to be a people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the head of Ephraim is Samaria, and the head of Samaria is the
        son of Remaliah. If you do not believe then you will not endure.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Yahweh continued to speak to Ahaz, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAsk for a sign for yourself from Yahweh God; make it deep as
        Sheol or make it high as above.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Ahaz said, \u201CI will not ask, and I will not put Yahweh to
        the test.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then he said, \u201CHear, house of David! Is it too little for you
        to make men weary, that you should also make my God weary? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore the Lord himself will give you a sign. Look! the virgin
        is with child and she is about to give birth to a son, and she shall call
        his name \u2018God with us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He shall eat curds and honey until he knows to reject the evil and
        to choose the good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: That Day'
      title: That Day
      number: 16
      content: 'For before the boy knows to reject the evil and to choose the good,
        the land whose two kings you dread will be abandoned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYahweh will bring on you and on your people and on the house
        of your ancestor days that have not come since the day Ephraim departed from
        Judah: the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And this shall happen: On that day, Yahweh will whistle for the fly
        that is at the end of the stream of Egypt and the bee that is in the land
        of Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And all of them will come and settle in the rivers of the cliffs
        and in the clefts of the rocks and on all of the thornbushes and watering
        places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "On that day, the Lord will shave the head and the hair of the feet
        with a razor of the one hired from beyond the river\u2014with the king of
        Assyria\u2014and it will even take off the beard. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And this shall happen: on that day, a young man will keep a young
        cow of the herd and two sheep alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And this shall happen: because of the abundance of milk production,
        he will eat curds, for every one that is left in the midst of the land will
        eat curds and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And this shall happen on that day: Every place where there are a
        thousand vines for a thousand silver pieces will become briers, and it will
        be thornbushes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'One will go there with arrows and bow, for all of the land will be
        briers and thornbushes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And as for all of the hills that they hoed with the hoe, you will
        not go there, for fear of briers and thornbushes. And it will become like
        pastureland for cattle and overtrodden land for sheep. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Signs of the Assyrian Invasion'
      title: Signs of the Assyrian Invasion
      number: 1
      content: "Then Yahweh said to me, \u201CTake yourself a large tablet and write
        on it with a common stylus pen: Maher-Halal-Hash-Baz. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And I will require reliable witnesses as a witness for me: Uriah
        the priest and Zechariah son of Jeberekiah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I approached the prophetess, and she conceived, and she gave
        birth to a son. And Yahweh said to me, \u201CCall his name Maher-Halal-Hash-Baz. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Shiloah Waters and Euphrates Flood'
      title: Shiloah Waters and Euphrates Flood
      number: 4
      content: "For before the boy knows to call \u2018my father\u2019 and \u2018my
        mother,\u2019 one will carry away the wealth of Damascus and the spoil of
        Samaria in the presence of the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Yahweh continued to speak to me again, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBecause this people has refused the gently flowing waters of
        Shiloah and rejoices over Rezin and the son of Remaliah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'therefore look! The Lord is bringing up the waters of the great and
        mighty river against them, the king of Assyria and all his glory. And he
        will rise above all his channels, and he will flow over all his banks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he will sweep into Judah; he will overflow and he will flood
        up to the neck. He will reach, and he will spread his wings out over your
        entire land, God with us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Be broken, you peoples, and be dismayed. And listen, all distant
        parts of the earth; gird yourselves and be dismayed; gird yourselves and
        be dismayed! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Wait for Yahweh'
      title: Wait for Yahweh
      number: 10
      content: 'Make a plan, but it will be frustrated! Speak a word, but it will
        not stand, for God is with us! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For Yahweh said this to me while his hand weighed heavily on me, 
        and he warned me not to walk in the way of this people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou must not call conspiracy everything that this people calls
        conspiracy, and you must not share its fear, and you must not be in dread. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall regard Yahweh of hosts as holy, and he is your fear, and
        he is your dread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he will become like a sanctuary and a stumbling-stone, and like
        a stumbling-rock for the two houses of Israel, like a trap and a snare for
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And many shall stumble among them, and they shall fall and they shall
        be broken, and they shall be ensnared and they shall be caught.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Bind up the testimony; seal the teaching among my disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I will wait for Yahweh, who hides his face from the house of
        Jacob, and I will await him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Look! I and the children whom Yahweh has given to me are like signs
        and portents in Israel from Yahweh of hosts, the one who dwells on the mountain
        of Zion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now if they tell you, \u201CConsult the ghosts and the spirits, those
        who chirp and those who mutter. Should not a people consult its gods, the
        dead on behalf of the living, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "for teaching and for testimony?\u201D surely they who speak like
        this have no dawn.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And it will pass through it distressed and hungry, and this shall
        happen: when it is hungry, it will be enraged, and it will curse its king
        and its gods, and it will face upwar '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'or look to the earth. But look! Distress and darkness, the gloom
        of affliction! And it will be thrust into darkness! '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: New Light: The Birth of a King'
      title: 'New Light: The Birth of a King'
      number: 1
      content: ' But there will be no gloom for those who were in distress.  In former
        times he treated the land of Zebulun and Naphtali with contempt, but in the
        future he will honor the way of the sea beyond the Jordan, Galilee of the
        nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The people who walked in darkness have seen a great light; light
        has shined on those who lived in a land of darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You have made the nation numerous; you have not made the joy great.
        They rejoice in your presence as with joy at the harvest, as they rejoice
        when they divide plunder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For you have shattered the yoke of its burden and the stick of its
        shoulder, the rod of its oppressor, on the day of Midian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For every boot that marches and shakes the earth  and garment rolled
        in blood will be for burning\u2014fire fuel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For a child has been born for us; a son has been given to us. And
        the dominion will be on his shoulder, and his name is called Wonderful Counselor,
        Mighty God, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Yahweh\u2019s Anger against Arrogance"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Anger against Arrogance"
      number: 7
      content: 'His dominion will grow continually, and to peace there will be no
        end  on the throne of David and over his kingdom, to establish it and sustain
        it with justice and righteousness now and forever. The zeal of Yahweh of
        hosts will do this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord has sent out a word against Jacob, and it fell on Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And all of the people knew it, Ephraim and the inhabitants of Samaria
        in pride and arrogance of heart, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe bricks have fallen, but we will build with dressed stone.
        The sycamore-fig trees were felled, but we will replace them with cedars.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Yahweh strengthened the adversaries of Rezin against him, and
        he provoked his enemies\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Aram from the east and Philistines from the west\u2014 and they devoured
        Israel with the whole mouth. He has not turned away his anger in all of this,
        and his hand is still stretched out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the people did not turn to the one who struck it,  and they did
        not seek Yahweh of hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Yahweh cut off head and tail from Israel, palm branch and reed
        in one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Elders and the respectable are the head, and prophets who teach lies
        are the tail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the leaders of this people were misleading them, and those who
        were led were confused. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore the Lord did not rejoice over its young men, and he did
        not have compassion on its orphans and widows, for everyone was godless and
        an evildoer, and every mouth was speaking folly. In all of this his anger
        did not turn away, and still his hand is stretched out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For wickedness burned like fire; it consumed brier and thorn. And
        it kindled the thickets of the forest, and they swirled upward in a column
        of smoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The land was burned through the wrath of Yahweh of hosts, and the
        people became like fire fuel. People had no compassion toward each other.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They devoured on the right but still were hungry and devoured on
        the left but they were not satisfied. Each one devoured the flesh of his
        arm, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Manasseh devoured Ephraim, and Ephraim Manasseh; together they were
        against Judah. In all of this his anger has not turned away, and still his
        hand is stretched out. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woes on the Wicked'
      title: Woes on the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: 'Ah! Those who decree decrees of evil, and writers who have written
        harm, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'to guide the needy away from legal claims,  and to rob the justice
        from the poor of my people, to make widows their spoil; and they plunder
        orphans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And what will you do at the day of punishment, and at calamity? It
        comes from afar! To whom will you flee for help, and where will you leave
        your wealth, '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Judgment on Assyria\u2019s Arrogance"
      title: "Judgment on Assyria\u2019s Arrogance"
      number: 4
      content: 'save that they bow down under the prisoners and fall under the slain? 
        In all of this his anger has not turned away, and still his hand is stretched
        out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ah! Assyria, the rod of my anger, and a staff is in their hand: my
        wrath! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I send him against a godless nation, and I command him against the
        people of my wrath, to capture spoil and to carry off plunder, and to make
        them a trampling place, like the clay of the streets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But he does not think this,  and his heart does not plan this. For
        it is in his heart to destroy and to cut off not a few nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For he says, \u201CAre not my commanders altogether kings? "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Is not Calno like Carchemish? Is not Hamath like Arpad? Is not Samaria
        like Damascus? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As my hand has reached to the kingdoms of the idols  \u2014and their
        images were greater than those of Jerusalem and Samaria\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "shall I not do to Jerusalem and its idols what I have done to Samaria
        and her idols?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And this shall happen: when the Lord has finished all his work against
        Mount Zion and Jerusalem, \u201CI will punish the arrogance of the king of
        Assyria and his haughtiness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For he says, \u201CI have done it by the strength of my hand and
        by my wisdom, for I have understanding, and I have removed the boundaries
        of peoples, and I have plundered their stores, and like a bull I have brought
        down the inhabitants.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And my hand has found, like a nest, the wealth of the peoples, and
        like the gathering of forsaken eggs, I myself have gathered all the earth.
        And there was no fluttering wing or open mouth or chirp.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Does the ax boast against the one who cuts with it, or the saw magnify
        itself against the one who moves it to and fro? As if a rod should move the
        one who lifts it!  As if a staff should lift up that which is not wood!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore the Lord, Yahweh of hosts, will send leanness among his
        sturdy warriors, and a burning like the burning of fire will burn under his
        glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the light of Israel will become like a fire, and his holy one
        like a flame, and it will burn and devour his thorns and briers in one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he will destroy the glory of his forest and orchard completely, 
        and it will be like the wasting away of one who is sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Return of the Remnant'
      title: The Return of the Remnant
      number: 19
      content: 'And the rest of the trees of his forest will be a small number, and
        a boy can write them down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And this shall happen: on that day, the remnant of Israel and the
        survivors of the house of Jacob will not continue to lean on the one who
        struck it but will lean on Yahweh, the holy one of Israel, in truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "A remnant will return\u2014 the remnant of Jacob\u2014to the mighty
        God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For though your people Israel was like the sand of the sea, only
        a remnant of it will return. Annihilation is determined, overflowing with
        righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the Lord Yahweh of hosts is about to make a complete destruction
        and a determined end in the midst of all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord Yahweh of hosts: \u201CMy people who
        live in Zion, you must not be afraid of Assyria. It beats you with the rod,
        and it lifts up its staff against you as the Egyptians did.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "My indignation will come to an end in just a very little while, 
        and my anger will be directed to their destruction.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Yahweh of hosts is going to swing a whip against him, as when
        Midian was defeated at the rock of Oreb; and his staff will be over the sea,
        and he will lift him up as he did in Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And this shall happen: on that day, he will remove his burden from
        your shoulder and his yoke from your neck, and a yoke will be destroyed because
        of fat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He has come to Aiath, he has passed through Migron; at Micmash he
        deposited his baggage. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'They crossed over the pass; Geba is a place of overnight lodging
        for us. Ramah trembles; Gibeah of Saul has fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Daughter of Gallim, cry out with your voice; Laishah, listen! Anathoth
        is poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Madmenah flees! The inhabitants of Gebim bring themselves into safety! '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'This day taking a stand at Nob, he will shake his fist at the mountain
        of the daughter of Zion, at the hill of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Look! The Lord Yahweh of hosts is about to lop off the branches with
        great power, and the towering trees will be felled, and the tall trees will
        be brought low. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And he will cut down the thickets of the forest with the axe, and
        Lebanon will fall by the mighty one. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Branch\u2019s Righteous Reign"
      title: "The Branch\u2019s Righteous Reign"
      number: 1
      content: 'And a shoot will come out from the stump of Jesse, and a branch from
        its roots will bear fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the spirit of Yahweh shall rest on him\u2014 a spirit of wisdom
        and understanding, a spirit of counsel and might, a spirit of knowledge and
        the fear of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And his breath is in the fear of Yahweh. And he shall judge not by
        his eyesight, and he shall rebuke not by what he hears with his ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But he shall judge the poor with righteousness, and he shall decide
        for the needy of the earth with rectitude. And he shall strike the earth
        with the rod of his mouth, and he shall kill the wicked person with the breath
        of his lips. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And righteousness shall be the belt around his waist, and faithfulness
        the belt around his loins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And a wolf shall stay with a lamb, and a leopard shall lie down with
        a kid, and a calf and a lion and a fatling together as a small boy leads
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And a cow and a bear shall graze; their young shall lie down together.
        And a lion shall eat straw like the cattle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And an infant shall play over a serpent\u2019s hole, and a toddler
        shall put his hand on a viper\u2019s hole. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They will not injure and they will not destroy on all of my holy
        mountain,  for the earth will be full of the knowledge of Yahweh, as the
        waters cover the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Regathered Remnant'
      title: The Regathered Remnant
      number: 10
      content: 'And this shall happen on that day: the nations shall inquire of the
        root of Jesse, which shall be standing as a signal to the peoples, and his
        resting place shall be glorious. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And this shall happen on that day: The Lord will again extend his
        hand a second time to acquire the remnant of his people that is left, from
        Assyria, Egypt, Pathros, Cush, Elam, Shinar, Hamath, and the coastlands of
        the sea, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and he will raise a signal for the nations. And he will gather the
        outcasts of Israel, and he will gather the scattered ones of Judah together
        from the four corners of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the jealousy of Ephraim shall depart, and the enemies of Judah
        shall be cut off. Ephraim shall not be jealous of Judah, and Judah shall
        not be an enemy of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But they shall swoop upon the Philistine shoulder, westward.  Together
        they shall plunder the sons of the east. Edom and Moab will be under their
        command,  and the sons of Ammon will be their subjugated people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Yahweh will divide the tongue of the sea of Egypt,  and he will
        wave his hand over the river with his scorching wind; and he will strike
        it into seven streams, and he will make it passable by foot.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So there shall be a highway from Assyria for the remnant of his people
        that remains, as there was for Israel when it went up from the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Song of Thanksgiving'
      title: A Song of Thanksgiving
      number: 1
      content: "And you will say on that day, \u201CI will give you thanks, Yahweh,
        for though you were angry with me, your anger turned away, and you comforted
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Look! God is my salvation; I will trust, and I will not be afraid,
        for my strength and might is Yah, Yahweh; and he has become salvation for
        me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you will draw water from the wells of salvation in joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you will say on that day, \u201CGive thanks to Yahweh; call on
        his name. Make his deeds known among the peoples; bring to remembrance that
        his name is exalted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Sing praises to Yahweh, for he has done a glorious thing; this is
        known in all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Inhabitant of Zion, shout out and sing for joy, for the holy one
        of Israel is great in your midst.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: An Oracle against Babylon'
      title: An Oracle against Babylon
      number: 1
      content: 'The oracle of Babylon that Isaiah son of Amoz saw: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Raise a signal on a bare hill, lift up your voice to them; wave the
        hand and may they enter the gateways of the noblemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I myself I have commanded my consecrated ones, I have also summoned
        my mighty warriors concerning my anger, the ones who exalt over my majesty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A sound, a noise is on the mountains, the likeness of many people!
        A sound of the roar of the kingdoms, of nations gathering! Yahweh of hosts
        is mustering an army for battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They are coming from a distant land, from the end of the heavens,
        Yahweh and the weapons of his indignation, to destroy the whole earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Wail, for the day of Yahweh is near; it will come like destruction
        from Shaddai!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore all hands will grow slack, and every human heart will melt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and they will be dismayed. Pangs and labor pains will seize them;
        they will tremble like a woman giving birth. They will stare at one another, 
        their faces flushing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Look! The day of Yahweh is coming, cruel and wrath and the burning
        of anger, to make the earth a desolation, and he will destroy its sinners
        from it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the stars of the heavens and their constellations will not flash
        forth their light; the sun will keep back when it comes out, and the moon
        will not cause its light to shine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I will punish the world for its evil and the wicked for their
        iniquity. And I will put an end to the pride of the arrogant, and I will
        bring the haughtiness of tyrants low. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will make humanity more rare than gold and humankind more than
        the gold of Ophir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore I will make the heavens tremble, and the earth will quake
        from its place because of the wrath of Yahweh of hosts, and in the day his
        anger burns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And this shall happen: like a hunted gazelle or sheep with none to
        gather them,  they will each turn to his own people, and they will each flee
        to his own land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Everyone who is found will be pierced through, and everyone who is
        carried away will fall by the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And their children will be dashed into pieces before their eyes;
        their houses will be plundered, and their wives will be raped.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Look! I am stirring the Medes up against them, who do not value silver
        and do not delight in gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And their bows will shatter young men. And they will not show mercy
        on the fruit of the womb; their eyes will not look compassionately on children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Babylon, the glory of kingdoms, the splendor of the Chaldeans\u2019
        pride, will be like when God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It will not be inhabited forever, and it will not be dwelled in forever; 
        and no Arab will pitch a tent there, and shepherds will not allow their flocks
        to lie down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But wild animals will lie down there, and their houses will be full
        of howling creatures, and the daughters of ostriches will live there, and
        goats will dance there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And hyenas will answer in its palaces, and jackals in the pleasure
        palaces; and its time is coming soon,  and its days will not be prolonged. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Restoration of Israel'
      title: The Restoration of Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'But Yahweh will have compassion on Jacob, and he will again choose
        Israel and set them on their land, and the immigrant will join himself to
        them, and they will attach themselves to the house of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: The Downfall of the King of Babylon'
      title: The Downfall of the King of Babylon
      number: 2
      content: 'And the nations will take them and bring them to their place, and
        the house of Israel will take possession of them in the land of Yahweh as
        slaves and female slaves. And this will happen: they will take their captors
        captive and rule over their oppressors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And it shall happen on the day Yahweh gives you rest from your pain
        and turmoil and hard labor which you had to perform,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "that you will take this taunt against the king of Babylon, and you
        will say: \u201CHow the oppressor has ceased! his insolence has ceased. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yahweh has broken the staff of the wicked, the scepter of rulers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'that struck the peoples in wrath, a blow without ceasing, that ruled
        the nations in anger with unrestrained persecution.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All of the earth rests and is quiet; they break forth into singing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Even the cypresses rejoice over you, the cedars of Lebanon: \u2018Since
        you were laid down, no wood cutter comes up against us.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Sheol below is getting excited over you, to meet you when you come; 
        it arouses the dead spirits for you, all of the leaders of the earth. It
        raises all of the kings of the nations from their thrones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "All of them will respond and say to you, \u2018You yourself also
        were made weak like us! You have become the same as us!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Your pride is brought down to Sheol, and the sound of your harps;
        maggots are spread out beneath you like a bed, and your covering is worms.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'How you have fallen from heaven, morning star, son of dawn! You are
        cut down to the ground, conqueror of nations! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And you yourself said in your heart, \u2018I will ascend to heaven;
        I will raise up my throne above the stars of God; and I will sit on the mountain
        of assembly on the summit of Zaphon;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will ascend to the high places of the clouds,  I will make myself
        like the Most High.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But you are brought down to Sheol, to the depths of the pit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Those who see you will stare at you, they will look closely at you:
        \u2018Is this the man who made the earth tremble, who caused kingdoms to
        shake, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "who made the world like the desert and destroyed its cities, who
        would not let his prisoners go home?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'All the kings of the nations, all of them, lie in glory, each one
        in his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But as for you, you are thrown away from your grave, like an abhorrent
        shoot, clothed with the slain, those pierced by the sword, those who go down
        to the stones of the pit, like a corpse that is trodden down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You will not be united with them in burial because you have destroyed
        your land, you have killed your people. The descendants of evildoers will
        not be mentioned for eternity! '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Prepare a place of slaughter for his sons because of the sin of their
        ancestors.  Let them not rise and take possession of the earth or fill up
        the face of the world with cities.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAnd I will rise up against them,\u201D declares Yahweh of hosts,
        \u201Cand I will cut off name and a remnant from Babylon, and offspring and
        posterity,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Oracle of Judgment on Assyria'
      title: Oracle of Judgment on Assyria
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CAnd I will make her a possession of the hedgehog, and pools
        of water, and I will sweep her away with the broom of destruction,\u201D
        declares Yahweh of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Yahweh of hosts has sworn, saying, \u201CSurely just as I have intended,
        so it shall be. And just as I have planned, it shall stand: "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "to break Assyria in my land, and I will trample him down on my mountains;
        and he shall remove his yoke from them, and he shall remove his burden from
        his shoulders.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'This is the plan that is planned concerning all of the earth; and
        this is the hand that is stretched out over all of the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Oracle of Judgment on Philistia'
      title: Oracle of Judgment on Philistia
      number: 27
      content: 'For Yahweh of hosts has planned, and who will frustrate it? And his
        hand is stretched out, and who will turn it back? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'In the year of the death of king Ahaz there was this oracle: '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You must not rejoice, all you Philistines, that the rod that struck
        you is broken, for a viper will come forth from the root of the snake, and
        its fruit will be a flying serpent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the firstborn of the poor will graze, and the needy will lie
        down in security; but I will cause your root to die in famine, and it will
        kill your remnant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Wail, gate! Cry, city! Melt, Philistia, all of you! For smoke is
        coming from the north, and there is no straggler in his ranks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And what will one answer the messengers of the nation? That Yahweh
        has founded Zion, and the needy of his people will take refuge in it. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Oracle of Judgment on Moab'
      title: Oracle of Judgment on Moab
      number: 1
      content: 'An oracle of Moab: Because Ar is devastated in a night, Moab is destroyed;
        because Kir of Moab is devastated in a night, it is destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It has gone up to the house,  and Dibon to the high places for weeping
        over Nebo, and Moab wails over Medeba. Every head is bald,  every beard is
        shaved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They gird themselves with sackcloth in its streets; on its roofs
        and public squares everyone wails, going down in weeping. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Heshbon and Elealeh cry out, their voice is heard as far as Jahaz;
        therefore the armed ones of Moab cry out; its soul quivers for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My heart cries out for Moab; its fugitives flee up to Zoar, to Eglath-shelishiyah.
        For at the ascent of Luhith it goes up it with weeping; for on the road of
        Horonaim they raise up a cry of destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the waters of Nimrim are wastelands; for the grass has withered,
        the vegetation has vanished, there is no greenness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore they carry the abundance it has made and their store of
        goods over the river of the poplars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For a cry for help has encircled the territory of Moab, her wailing
        is heard as far as Eglaim, and her wailing as far as Beer Elim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the waters of Dimon are full of blood; but I will place added
        things upon Dimon: a lion for the survivors of Moab and for the remnant of
        the land. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Send a ram to the ruler of the land, from Sela across the desert
        to the mountain of daughter Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And this shall be: like a bird fleeing from a thrust away nest shall
        be the daughters of Moab at the fords of Arnon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CBring counsel, make a decision; make your shade like the night
        in the middle of noonday. Hide the outcasts; you must not betray the fugitive. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Let my outcasts of Moab dwell as aliens among you; be a hiding place
        for them from the presence of the destroyer.\u201D When the oppressor is
        no more, destruction has stopped, the one who tramples has disappeared from
        the land, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then a throne shall be established in steadfast love, and one shall
        sit on it in faithfulness, in the tent of David, judging and seeking justice
        and zealous for righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "We have heard of the pride of Moab\u2014exceedingly proud\u2014 of
        his arrogance, pride, and insolence; his boasting is not true.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore Moab wails; all of it wails for Moab, for the raisin cakes
        of Kir-hareseth you moan, utterly devastated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For Heshbon withers the fields, the vine of Sibmah; rulers of nations
        have broken down her tendrils, they reached up to Jazer, they wandered to
        the desert; her shoots spread abroad, they crossed over the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore I weep with the weeping of Jazer for the vine of Sibmah.
        I drench you with my tears, Heshbon and Elealeh, for a jubilant shout has
        fallen over your summer fruit and harvest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And joy and gladness are taken away from the fruitful land, and in
        the vineyards no one exults, no one shouts for joy; no treader treads wine
        in the presses; I have put to an end to the jubilant shout. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore my heart moans like a harp for Moab and my inner parts
        for Kir-heres. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And this shall happen: when Moab appears, when it is weary upon the
        high place and it comes to its sanctuary to pray, it will not prevail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This was the word that Yahweh spoke to Moab in the past.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now Yahweh speaks, saying, \u201CIn three years, like the years
        of a hired worker, the glory of Moab will become contemptible, with all of
        the great multitude, and the remnant will be a few, small, not strong. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Oracle of Judgment on Damascus'
      title: Oracle of Judgment on Damascus
      number: 1
      content: "An oracle of Damascus: \u201CLook! Damascus will cease being a city
        and will become a heap of ruins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The cities of Aroer will be deserted;  they will be for the flocks,
        and they will lie down and no one will frighten them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the fortified city will disappear from Ephraim, and the kingdom
        from Damascus; and the remnant of Aram will be like the glory of the children
        of Israel,\u201D declares Yahweh of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAnd this shall happen: On that day, the glory of Jacob will
        be brought low, and the fat of his flesh will become lean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And it shall be as when a reaper gathers standing grain and he reaps
        grain with his arm, and it shall be like one who gathers ears of grain in
        the valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And gleanings will be left over in it, as when an olive tree is beaten, 
        two or three ripe olive berries in the top of a branch, four or five on its
        fruitful branches,\u201D declares Yahweh, the God of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'On that day, mankind will look to its maker, and its eyes will look
        to the holy one of Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'it will not look to the altars, the work of its hands, and it will
        not see what its fingers made and the poles of Asherah worship and the incense
        altars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'On that day, its fortified cities will be like the abandonment of
        the wooded place and the summit, which they deserted because of the children
        of Israel; and there will be desolation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For you have forgotten the God of your salvation, and you have not
        remembered the rock of your refuge; therefore you plant plants of pleasantness,
        and you plant a vine of a foreigner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Roar of the Peoples'
      title: The Roar of the Peoples
      number: 11
      content: 'On your planting day you make them grow, and in the morning of your
        sowing you bring them into bloom, yet the harvest will flee in a day of sickness
        and incurable pain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Ah! The noise of many peoples, they make a noise like the noise of
        the seas! And the roar of nations, they roar like the roar of mighty waters! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The nations roar like the roar of many waters, but he will rebuke
        him, and he will flee far away. And they are chased like chaff of the mountains
        before the wind and like tumbleweed before the storm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'At the time of evening, and look, terror! Before morning he is no
        more. This is the fate of those who plunder us and the lot of those who plunder
        us. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Oracle of Judgment on Cush'
      title: Oracle of Judgment on Cush
      number: 1
      content: 'Ah! land of the whirring of wings, which is beyond the rivers of
        Cush, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that sends messengers by the sea and in vessels of papyrus on the
        surface of the waters! Go, swift messengers, to a tall and smooth nation,
        to a people feared near and far,  a mighty, mighty and trampling nation,
        whose land rivers divide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All you inhabitants of the world and dwellers of the earth, when
        a signal is raised on the mountains, you must look, and when a trumpet is
        blown, you must listen! '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For Yahweh said this to me: \u201CI will be quiet, and I will look
        from my dwelling place like clear heat because of light,  like a cloud of
        dew in the heat of harvest.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For before the harvest, when the blossom is complete  and a blossom
        becomes ripening fruit, and one cuts off the shoots with pruning hooks, and
        one removes, tears away the tendrils. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They shall all be left for birds of prey of the mountains and for
        the animals of the earth. And the birds of prey will pass the summer on it,
        and every animal of the earth will winter on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'At that time, a gift will be brought to Yahweh of hosts from a tall
        and smooth people, and from a people feared near and far, a mighty, mighty
        and trampling nation, whose land the rivers divide, to the place of the name
        of Yahweh of hosts, the mountain of Zion. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Oracle of Judgment on Egypt'
      title: Oracle of Judgment on Egypt
      number: 1
      content: 'An oracle of Egypt: Look! Yahweh is riding on a swift cloud and is
        coming to Egypt. And the idols of Egypt will tremble in front of him, and
        the heart of Egypt melts in his inner parts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CAnd I will stir up Egyptians against Egyptians,  and each one
        will fight against his brother and each one against his neighbor, city against
        city, kingdom against kingdom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the spirit of the Egyptians will be disturbed in his midst, and
        I will confuse his plans,  and they will consult the idols and the spirits
        of the dead, and the ghosts and the spiritists. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I will hand over the Egyptians into the hand of a hard master,
        and a powerful king will rule over them,\u201D declares the Lord Yahweh of
        hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the waters will be dried up from the sea, and the river will
        be parched and dry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the rivers will become foul-smelling; the branches of the Nile
        of Egypt will become little and dry up; reed and rush will wither. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Bare places by the Nile will be dried up, by the edge of the Nile
        and all the sown land of the Nile; it will be driven about, and it will be
        no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the fishers will mourn, and all of those who cast fishhooks in
        the Nile will lament, and those who spread out fishing nets on the surface
        of the water will languish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the workers of combed flax will be ashamed, and those who weave
        white linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And her weavers will be crushed; all the hired workers will be grieved
        of heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Surely the princes of Zoan are foolish; the wise of the counselors
        of Pharaoh give senseless counsel. How can you say to Pharaoh, \u201CI myself
        am a son of sages, a descendant of ancient kings\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Where are your sages then? Now, let them tell you, and let them know
        what Yahweh of hosts has planned against Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The princes of Zoan have become foolish; the princes of Memphis are
        deceived; the leaders of her tribes have led Egypt astray. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Yahweh has mixed a spirit of confusion into her midst, and they have
        caused Egypt to stagger in all of its doings, as when a drunkard staggers
        in his vomit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Future Blessing of Egypt, Assyria, and Egypt'
      title: The Future Blessing of Egypt, Assyria, and Egypt
      number: 15
      content: 'And there will be nothing for Egypt to do,  head or tail, palm branch
        or reed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'On that day, Egypt will be like women, and will tremble and be afraid
        before the waving hand of Yahweh of hosts that he is waving against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the land of Judah will become a terror to Egypt, everyone to
        whom one mentions it will be afraid in himself because of the plan of Yahweh
        of hosts that he is planning against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "On that day, there will be five cities in the land of Egypt that
        speak the language of Canaan and swear an oath to Yahweh of hosts. One will
        be called \u201CCity of the Sun.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'On that day, there will be an altar for Yahweh in in the middle of
        the land of Egypt, and a stone pillar for Yahweh at her border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And it will be a sign and a witness to Yahweh of hosts in the land
        of Egypt; when they cry out to Yahweh because of oppressors, he will send
        them a savior and a defender, and he will deliver them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Yahweh will make himself known to Egypt, and Egypt will know
        Yahweh on that day, and they will worship with sacrifice and offering, and
        they will make vows to Yahweh, and they will fulfill them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Yahweh will strike Egypt, striking and healing; and they will
        return to Yahweh, and he will respond to their prayer, and he will heal them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'On that day, there will be a highway from Egypt to Assyria, and Assyria
        will come into Egypt, and Egypt into Assyria, and Egypt will worship together
        with Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'On that day, Israel will be the third with Egypt and Assyria, a blessing
        in the midst of the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "whom Yahweh of hosts blessed, saying, \u201CMay Egypt my people be
        blessed, and Assyria, the work of my hands, and my inheritance, Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Sign regarding Egypt and Cush'
      title: A Sign regarding Egypt and Cush
      number: 1
      content: 'In the year the commander-in-chief came to Ashdod, when Sargon the
        king of Assyria sent him, and he fought against Ashdod and he took it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "at that time, Yahweh had spoken by the hand of Isaiah son of Amoz,
        saying, \u201CGo and loosen the sackcloth from your loins, and take off your
        sandals from your feet,\u201D and he had done so, walking naked and barefoot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Yahweh said, \u201CJust as my servant Isaiah has walked naked
        and barefoot three years as a sign and a portent against Egypt and Cush, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'so shall the king of Assyria lead the captives of Egypt and the exiles
        of Cush, young and old, naked and barefoot, with bared buttocks, the shame
        of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And they shall be dismayed, and they shall be ashamed because of
        Cush, their hope, and because of Egypt, their pride. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the inhabitant of the coastland will say this on that day: \u2018Look!
        This is our hope to whom we fled for help, to be delivered from the king
        of Assyria, and how shall we escape?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Babylon'
      title: The Fall of Babylon
      number: 1
      content: 'The oracle of the wilderness of the sea: As storm winds passing over
        in the Negev, it comes from the desert, from a frightful land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A hard revelation is told to me; the treacherous deals treacherously,
        and the destroyer destroys. Go up, Elam; lay siege, Media! I put an end to
        all of her sighing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore my loins are filled with anguish; pangs have seized me,
        like the pangs of a woman giving birth. I am too bent to hear,  I am too
        dismayed to see.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'My mind staggers; fear terrifies me; the twilight I desired brought
        me fear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Set out the table in order! Spread out the rugs!  Eat! drink! Rise
        up, commanders; smear the shield! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord said this to me: \u201CGo, set a watchman in position.
        He must announce what he sees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When he sees riders,  a pair of horsemen, riders of donkeys,  riders
        of camels,  then he must listen attentively, paying attention, paying special
        attention.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the watchman called, \u201CLord, I am standing on the watchtower
        continually by day, and I am standing at my post throughout the night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And look at this! A man\u2019s a chariot is coming, a pair of horsemen!\u201D
        Then he responded and said, \u201CIt has fallen! Babylon has fallen! And
        all the images of her gods are smashed on the ground!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Oracle regarding Dumah'
      title: Oracle regarding Dumah
      number: 10
      content: 'My downtrodden people and the son of my threshing floor, I will announce
        to you what I have heard from Yahweh of hosts, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The oracle of Dumah: One is calling to me from Seir, \u201CWatchman,
        what of the night? Watchman, what of the night?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Oracle against Arabia'
      title: Oracle against Arabia
      number: 12
      content: "The watchman says, \u201CMorning comes, and also the night. If you
        will inquire, inquire; come back again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'An oracle concerning Arabia: You will spend the night in the thicket
        in a desert-plateau,  caravans of Dedanites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When you happen to meet the thirsty, bring water. Inhabitants of
        the land of Tema came to meet the fugitive with his bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For they have fled from the swords, from the drawn sword and the
        bent bow, and from the heaviness of the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For the Lord said this to me: \u201CIn one more year, like the years
        of a hired worker, all the glory of Kedar will come to an end. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the remainder of the number of the bows of the warriors of the
        sons of Kedar will be few.\u201D For Yahweh, the God of Israel, has spoken. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Oracle against Jerusalem'
      title: Oracle against Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'The oracle of the valley of vision: What business do you have going
        up, all of you, to the roofs, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'noisy, tumultuous city, exultant town? Your slain are not slain by
        the sword, nor are they dead from battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All of your rulers have fled together without a bow; all of you who
        were found were captured. They were captured together; they had fled far
        away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore I said, \u201CLook away from me, let me weep bitterly; 
        you must not insist on comforting me for the destruction of the daughter
        of my people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the Lord Yahweh of hosts has a day of tumult and trampling and
        confusion in the valley of vision, a tearing down of walls and a cry for
        help to the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Elam lifted up the quiver, with chariots of men and cavalry.
        And Kir uncovered the shield. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And this happened: the choicest of your valleys were full of chariots, 
        and the cavalry confidently stood at the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he uncovered the covering of Judah. And you looked, on that day,
        to the weapons of the House of the Forest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and you saw that the breaches in the walls of the city of David were
        many, and you gathered the waters of the lower pool. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And you counted the houses of Jerusalem, and you broke down the houses
        to fortify the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you made a reservoir between the walls for the waters of the
        old pool, but you did not look to its maker, and you did not see the one
        who created it long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the Lord, Yahweh of hosts, called on that day for weeping and
        mourning, and for baldness and girding with sackcloth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But look! Joy and gladness, the killing of oxen and the slaughtering
        of sheep, the eating of meat and the drinking of wine! \u201CLet us eat and
        drink, for tomorrow we die!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Oracle regarding Shebna'
      title: Oracle regarding Shebna
      number: 14
      content: "And it was revealed in my ears by Yahweh of hosts: \u201CSurely this
        sin will not be atoned for you until you die!\u201D says the Lord, Yahweh
        of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The Lord, Yahweh of hosts, says this: \u201CGo! Go to this steward,
        to Shebna, who is over the house: "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018What business do you have here, and who do you have here, that
        you have cut a grave cutting here for yourself, carving his grave on the
        height, a dwelling place for him in the rock? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Look! Yahweh is about to really hurl you, man! And he is about to
        grasp you firmly; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "he will wind a winding tightly around you like a ball, to a wide
        land.  There you shall die, and there the chariots of your splendor will
        be, disgrace to your master\u2019s house! "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will push you from your office, and he will throw you down
        from your position. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And this shall happen: On that day I will call to my servant, Eliakim
        son of Hilkiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and I will clothe him with your tunic, and I will bind your sash
        firmly about him, and I will put your authority into his hand, and he shall
        be like a father to the inhabitants of Jerusalem and to the house of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And I will put the key of the house of David on his shoulder, and
        he shall open and no one will be able to shut; and he shall shut and no one
        will be able to open. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And I will drive him in like a peg into a secure place, and he will
        become like a throne of glory to the house of his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they will hang all of the heaviness of his father\u2019s house
        on him, the offspring and the offshoot, all of the small vessels, from the
        bowls to the jars.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "On that day, declares Yahweh of hosts, the peg that was driven will
        move away into a secure place, and it will be cut down and fall, and the
        load that was on her will be cut off. For Yahweh has spoken.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Oracle against Tyre'
      title: Oracle against Tyre
      number: 1
      content: 'The oracle of Tyre: Wail, ships of Tarshish, for the house is destroyed
        so that no one can enter;  it is announced to them from the land of Cyprus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Be still, inhabitants of the coast, merchant of Sidon, who travels
        over the sea, they filled you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And on the great waters is the seed of Shihor, the harvest of the
        Nile is its produce, and she was the merchandise of the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Be ashamed, Sidon, for the sea, the fortress of the sea said, saying,
        \u201CI was not in labor, and I have not given birth, and I have not reared
        young men, brought up young women.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the report comes to Egypt, they will be in anguish at the report
        about Tyre. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Cross over to Tarshish! Wail, inhabitants of the coast! '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Is this your exultant one, her origin from the days of long ago?
        Her feet brought her to dwell afar as an alien. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who has planned this against Tyre, the bestower of crowns,  whose
        merchants were princes, her traders the honored ones of the earth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Yahweh of hosts has planned it: to defile the pride of all glory,
        to humble all the honored ones of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Cross over your own land like the Nile, daughter of Tarshish; there
        is no longer a harbor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He has stretched his hand out over the sea; he has made kingdoms
        shake. Yahweh has commanded concerning Canaan to destroy her fortresses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said, \u201CYou will not continue to exult, crushed one, virgin
        daughter of Sidon. Arise, cross over to Cyprus! There will be no rest for
        you even there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Look at the land of the Chaldeans! This people no longer exists.
        Assyria destined it for wild animals. They erected its siege towers; they
        demolished its citadel fortresses. It made her like a ruin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Wail, ships of Tarshish! For your fortress is destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And this will happen on that day: And Tyre will be forgotten seventy
        years,  like the days of one king. At the end of seventy years, it will be
        for Tyre like the song of the prostitute: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CTake a harp, go around the city, forgotten prostitute! Do it
        well, playing a stringed instrument! Make numerous songs, that you may be
        remembered.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And this shall happen: at the end of seventy years, Yahweh will visit
        Tyre, and she will return to her harlot\u2019s wages, and she will commit
        fornication with all the kingdoms of the world on the face of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And this shall happen: her merchandise and her harlot\u2019s wages
        will be set apart for Yahweh; it will not be stored up, and it will not be
        hoarded, but her merchandise will be for those who live before the presence
        of Yahweh, for eating to satiation and for fine clothing. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Judgment on the Earth'
      title: The Judgment on the Earth
      number: 1
      content: 'Look! Yahweh is about to lay the earth waste and is about to devastate
        it, and he will twist her surface, and he will scatter her inhabitants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it shall be as with the people, so with the priest; as with the
        slave, so with his master; as with the female slave, so with her mistress;
        as with the buyer, so with the seller; as with the lender, so with the borrower;
        as with the creditor, so with the one to whom he lends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The earth shall be utterly laid waste, and it shall be utterly plundered,
        for Yahweh has spoken this word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The earth dries up, it withers; the world languishes, it withers.
        The elevated of the people of the earth languish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and the earth is defiled beneath its inhabitants. For they have transgressed
        laws; they have passed by statutes;  they have broken the everlasting covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore a curse devours the earth, and the inhabitants in it suffer
        for their guilt. Therefore the inhabitants of the earth burn, and few men
        are left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The new wine dries up; the vine languishes. All the merry of heart
        sigh; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the joy of the tambourine has stopped. The noise of the jubilant
        has ceased; the joy of the lyre has stopped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They do not drink wine with song; strong drink is bitter to those
        who drink it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The city of emptiness is broken; every house is shut so that no one
        can enter;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'there is an outcry over the wine in the streets. All joy turns into
        darkness;  the joy of the earth disappears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Desolation is left in the city; the gate is crushed into a state
        of ruin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For it shall be like this in the midst of the earth, among the nations,
        like the beating of an olive tree, like gleanings when a grape harvest is
        at an end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They lift up their voices; they sing for joy; they shout out from
        the west over the majesty of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore glorify Yahweh in the east, the name of Yahweh the God
        of Israel in the coastlands of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "We hear songs from the edge of the earth: \u201CGlory to the righteous
        one!\u201D But I say, \u201CRuin to me! Ruin to me! Woe to me! The treacherous
        ones deal treacherously, and the treacherous ones deal treacherously with
        treachery!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Terror and the pit and the snare are upon you, inhabitants of the
        earth! '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And this shall happen: The one who flees from the sound of the terror
        shall fall into the pit, and the one who goes up from inside the pit shall
        be caught in the snare, for the windows from heaven are opened, and the foundations
        of the earth tremble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The earth is utterly broken; the earth is torn asunder; the earth
        is shaken violently. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The earth staggers to and fro like the drunkard, and it sways like
        a hut, and its transgression is heavy upon it, and it falls and does not
        rise again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And this shall happen on that day: Yahweh will punish the host of
        heaven in heaven, and the kings of the earth on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And they will be gathered in a gathering, like a prisoner in a pit.
        And they will be shut in a prison and be punished after many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the full moon will be ashamed and the sun will be ashamed, for
        Yahweh of hosts will rule on Mount Zion and in Jerusalem, and before his
        elders in glory. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Praise for Salvation'
      title: Praise for Salvation
      number: 1
      content: 'Yahweh, you are my God; I will exalt you. I will praise your name,
        for you have done wonderful things,  plans of old, in faithfulness, trustworthiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For you have made the city a heap, the fortified city a ruin, the
        palace of foreigners is no longer a city; it will never be rebuilt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore strong peoples will glorify you; a city of ruthless nations,
        they will fear you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For you have been a refuge to the poor, a refuge to the needy in
        his distress, a shelter from the rainstorm, a shade from the heat. For the
        breath of the ruthless was like a rainstorm against a wall,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'the noise of foreigners like heat in a dry land. You subdued the
        heat with the shade of a cloud; the song of the ruthless was silenced. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And on this mountain Yahweh of hosts will make for all peoples a
        rich feast,  a feast of aged wines, fat filled with marrow, filtered aged
        wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And on this mountain he will destroy the face of the shroud, the
        shroud over all peoples, and the woven covering over all nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He will destroy death forever, and the Lord Yahweh will wipe off
        the tears from all faces, and he will remove the disgrace of his people from
        all the earth, for Yahweh has spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And one will say, on that day, \u201CLook! This is our God! We have
        waited for him and he saved us! This is Yahweh; we waited for him! Let us
        be glad, and let us rejoice in his salvation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the hand of Yahweh will rest on this mountain, and Moab shall
        be trampled down under him as a heap of straw is trampled down in waters
        of a dung heap. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it will spread out its hands in the midst of it, just as the
        swimmer spreads out to swim, and its pride will be brought low with the movement
        of its hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he will throw down the fortification of the high point of your
        walls; he will bring it low; he will send it to the ground, to the dust. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Song of Praise"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Song of Praise"
      number: 1
      content: "On that day, this song will be sung in the land of Judah: \u201CWe
        have a strong city;  he sets up victory like walls and ramparts!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Open the gates so that the righteous nation who keeps faithfulness
        may enter! '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You will protect a firm inclination in peace, in peace because he
        trusts in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Trust in Yahweh forever, for in Yah, Yahweh you have an everlasting
        rock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For he has thrown down the inhabitants of the height, he lays low
        the lofty city. He lays it low to the ground; he throws her to the dust. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Yahweh\u2019s People Vindicated"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s People Vindicated"
      number: 6
      content: "The foot tramples it, the feet of the poor, the steps of the needy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The way of the righteous is a straight path; you clear the level
        path of the righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Surely we wait for you in the path of your judgments, Yahweh, for
        your name and renown are the desire of the soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I desire you with all my soul in the night; also I seek you with
        my spirit within me, for when your judgments are upon the earth, the inhabitants
        of the world learn righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Though the wicked person is shown compassion, he does not learn righteousness;
        he acts unjustly in the land of uprightness, and he does not see the majesty
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yahweh, though your hand reaches high, they do not see it. Let them
        see, and let them be ashamed of the zeal of people. Indeed, let the fire
        of your enemies consume them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yahweh, you will establish peace for us, for you have done even all
        of our works for us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yahweh, our God, lords besides you ruled over us, but we praise your
        name alone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The dead do not live; dead spirits do not rise because you have punished
        and destroyed them, and you have destroyed all memory of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You have added to the nation, Yahweh. You have added to the nation;
        you are honored. You have extended all the ends of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Yahweh, in distress they have visited you; they poured out an incantation; 
        your discipline was on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Like a pregnant woman on the point of giving birth, she writhes;
        she cries in her labor pains. So we were because of your presence, Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'We became pregnant, we writhed; we gave birth to wind. We cannot
        bring about deliverance on the earth, and no inhabitants of the world are
        born. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Your dead shall live; their corpses shall rise. Wake up and sing
        for joy, dwellers of the dust, for your dew is celestial dew,  and the earth
        will give birth to dead spirits.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Go, my people, enter into your chambers and shut your doors behind
        you; hide for a very little while, until the wrath has passed over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For look! Yahweh is about to come out from his place to punish the
        iniquity of the inhabitants of the earth against him, and the earth will
        disclose her blood and will no longer cover her slain. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Rescued'
      title: Israel Rescued
      number: 1
      content: 'On that day, Yahweh will punish with his cruel, great and strong
        sword Leviathan, the fleeing serpent, and Leviathan, the twisting serpent,
        and he will kill the sea monster that is in the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "On that day: \u201CA vineyard of beauty! Sing in praise of it! "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I, Yahweh, am her keeper; I water it again and again.  Lest one afflict
        harm on it, I guard it night and day; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I have no wrath.  Whatever gives me thorns and briers, I will step
        forth against in battle. I will set it on fire altogether. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Or let it grasp at my protection; let it make peace with me; peace
        let it make with me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Days are coming, let Jacob take root; Israel will blossom and send
        out shoots, and they will fill the face of the world with fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Does he strike him as he struck down those who struck him?  Or is
        he killed as those who killed him were killed?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'By expelling her, by her sending away, you argue with her. He removed
        them with his strong wind, in the day of the east wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore by this he will make atonement for the guilt of Jacob,
        and this will be all of the fruit of the removal of his sin: when he makes
        all the stones of the altar like crushed stones of chalk, no poles of Asherah
        worship or incense altars will stand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the fortified city is solitary, a settlement deserted and forsaken,
        like the wilderness; the calf grazes there, lies down there and destroys
        its branches. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When its branches are dry, they are broken; women are coming and
        setting light to it. For it is not a people of understanding; therefore his
        maker will not have compassion on him, and his creator will not show him
        favor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And this shall happen: on that day, Yahweh will thresh from the floodwaters
        of the Euphrates to the wadi of Egypt, and as for you, you will be gathered
        one by one, sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And this shall happen: on that day, a great trumpet will be blown,
        and those who were lost in the land of Assyria will come, and those who were
        scattered in the land of Egypt, and they will bow down to Yahweh on the holy
        mountain at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment against the Leaders of Ephraim'
      title: Judgment against the Leaders of Ephraim
      number: 1
      content: 'Ah! The garland of the pride of the drunkards of Ephraim and the
        withering flower of the glory of his beauty, which is at the head of the
        rich valley, ones overcome with wine! '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Look! The Lord has a mighty and strong one, like a rainstorm of hail,
        a wind storm of destruction, like a rainstorm of mighty overflowing waters,
        he will put them to the earth with his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The garland of the pride of the drunkards of Ephraim will be trampled
        by feet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and the withering flower of the glory of its beauty which is at the
        head of the rich valley will be like its early fig before summer, which the
        one who sees it swallows while it is still in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In that day, Yahweh of hosts will become a garland of glory and a
        diadem of beauty to the remnant of his people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and a spirit of justice to the one who sits over judgment, and strength
        to those who turn back the battle at the gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And these also stagger because of wine and stagger because of strong
        drink; priest and prophet stagger because of strong drink; they are confused
        because of wine. They stagger because of strong drink; they err in vision.
        They stagger in the rendering of a decision, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'for all the tables are full of disgusting vomit, with no place left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'To whom will he teach knowledge, and to whom will he explain the
        message? Those who are weaned from milk, those taken from the breast? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For it is blah-blah upon blah-blah, blah-blah upon blah-blah, gah-gah
        upon gah-gah, gah-gah upon gah-gah,  a little here, a little there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For he will speak with stammering and another tongue to this people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "to whom he has said, \u201CThis is rest; give rest to the weary;
        and this is repose\u201D; yet they were not willing to hear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Cornerstone of Zion'
      title: The Cornerstone of Zion
      number: 13
      content: 'And to them the word of Yahweh will be blah-blah upon blah-blah blah-blah
        upon blah-blah gah-gah upon gah-gah gah-gah upon gah-gah,  a little here,
        a little there, so that they may go and stumble backward and be broken and
        ensnared and captured. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore hear the word of Yahweh, men of mockery, rulers of these
        people in Jerusalem: '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Because you have said, \u201CWe have made a covenant with death,
        and we have made an agreement with Sheol. The overwhelming flood, when it
        passes through, will not come to us, for we have made lies our refuge, and
        we have hidden ourselves in falsehood.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore the Lord Yahweh says this: \u201CLook! I am laying a stone
        in Zion, a tested stone, a precious cornerstone, a founded foundation: \u2018The
        one who trusts will not panic.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I will make justice the measuring line, and righteousness the
        plumb line; and hail will sweep away the refuge of lies,  and waters will
        flood over the hiding place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And your covenant with death will be annulled, and your agreement
        with Sheol will not stand; you will become a trampling place for the overwhelming
        flood when it passes through. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "As often as it passes through, it will take you, for morning by morning
        it will pass through, in the day and in the night, and understanding the
        message will be only terror.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the bed is too short to stretch out on,  and the covering is
        too narrow when wrapping oneself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For Yahweh will rise up as at Mount Perazim; he will rave as in the
        valley at Gibeon to do his deed\u2014his deed is strange\u2014 and to work
        his work\u2014his work is alien! "
      comments: []
    - name: "22: A Parable of Yahweh\u2019s Work"
      title: "A Parable of Yahweh\u2019s Work"
      number: 22
      content: 'And now you must not scoff, or your bonds will be strong, for I have
        heard from the Lord, Yahweh of hosts: complete destruction decreed upon all
        the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Listen, and hear my voice! Listen attentively, and hear my word! '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Is it all day that the plowman plows, opens to sow seed, harrows
        his ground? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When he has leveled its surface, does he not scatter dill, and sow
        cumin seed, and plant wheat in planted rows,  and barley in an appointed
        place, and spelt grain as its border? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And his God instructs him about the prescription;  he teaches him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For dill is not threshed with a threshing sledge, nor is a wheel
        of a utility cart rolled over cumin, but dill is beaten out with a stick,
        and cumin with a rod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Grain is crushed fine, but certainly one does not thresh it forever;
        and one drives the wheel of his cart, but his horses do not crush it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'This also comes forth from Yahweh of hosts. He is wonderful in advice;
        he makes great wisdom. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Woe to Jerusalem'
      title: Woe to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'Ah! Ariel, Ariel, the city where David encamped! Add year to year,
        let festivals recur. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yet I will inflict Ariel, and there shall be mourning and lamentation,
        and it shall be to me like an altar hearth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And I will encamp in a circle against you, and I will lay siege to
        you with towers  and I will raise up siegeworks against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then you shall be low; you shall speak from the earth, and your words
        will be low, from dust. And your voice will be from the earth, like a ghost,
        and your word will whisper from the dust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the multitude of your strangers shall be like fine dust, and
        the multitude of tyrants like chaff that passes by. And it will happen in
        an instant, suddenly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You will be punished by Yahweh of hosts with thunder and earthquake
        and great sound, storm wind and tempest and the flame of a devouring fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the multitude of all the nations who fight against Ariel, all
        those who fight against her and her stronghold, and those who inflict her
        shall be like a dream, a vision of the night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And it shall be as when the hungry person dreams\u2014look, he is
        eating! And he wakes up and his inner self is empty. Or as when the thirsty
        person dreams\u2014look, he is drinking! And he wakes up and look, he is
        faint, and his inner self is longing for water. So shall be the multitude
        of all the nations who fight against Mount Zion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Be astonished and be amazed! Blind yourselves and be blinded! They
        are drunk but not from wine; they stagger but not from strong drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For Yahweh has poured out upon you a spirit of deep sleep, and he
        has shut your eyes, the prophets, and he has covered your heads, the seers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the vision of all this has become for you like the words of a
        sealed document. When they give it to one who knows the document, saying,
        \u201CRead this now!\u201D He says, \u201CI am not able, for it is sealed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And if the document is given to one who does not know how to read,
        saying, \u201CRead this now!\u201D he says, \u201CI do not know how to read.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CBecause this people draw near with its mouth,
        and with its lips it honors me, and its heart is far from me, and their fear
        of me is a commandment of men that has been taught, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "therefore look, I am again doing something spectacular and a spectacle
        with this spectacular people. And the wisdom of its wise men shall perish,
        and the discernment of its discerning ones shall keep itself hidden.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Ah! Those who make a plan deep, to hide it from Yahweh, and their
        deeds are in a dark place. And they say, \u201CWho sees us? And who knows
        us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Blessing after Punishment'
      title: Blessing after Punishment
      number: 16
      content: "Your perversity! As if a potter shall be regarded as the clay! That
        the product of its maker says, \u201CHe did not make me,\u201D and the thing
        made into shape says of its potter, \u201CHe has no understanding.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In a very little while shall not Lebanon change into a fruitful land,
        and the fruitful land be regarded as a forest? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And on that day, the deaf shall hear the words of a scroll, and the
        eyes of the blind shall see out of gloom and darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the meek have joy after joy in Yahweh, and the needy of the people
        shall rejoice in the holy one of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the tyrant shall be no more, and the scoffer shall come to an
        end. And all those lying in wait for evil shall be cut off; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'those who mislead a person into sin with a word and set a trap for
        the arbitrator in the gate and guide away the righteous by emptiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore Yahweh, who redeemed Abraham, says this to the house of
        Jacob: \u201CJacob will no longer be ashamed, and his face will no longer
        grow pale. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For when he sees his children, the work of my hands, in his midst,
        they will treat my name as holy, and they will treat the holy one of Jacob
        as holy, and they will stand in awe of the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And those who err in spirit will acquire understanding, and those
        who grumble will learn instruction. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning against Alliance with Egypt'
      title: Warning against Alliance with Egypt
      number: 1
      content: "\u201COh rebellious children!\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cto make
        a plan, but not from me, and pour out a libation, but not from my spirit,
        so as to add sin to sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Who go to go down to Egypt, but they do not ask of my mouth, to take
        refuge in the protection of Pharaoh and to take refuge in the shadow of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the protection of Pharaoh shall be shame to you, and the refuge
        in the shadow of Egypt, humiliation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For his officials are at Zoan, and his envoys reach to Hanes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Oracle regarding the Negev'
      title: Oracle regarding the Negev
      number: 5
      content: "Everyone will start to stink because of a people that cannot profit
        them, not for help and not for profiting, but for shame and also for disgrace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'An oracle of the animals of the Negev: Through a land of trouble
        and distress, of lioness and lion, among them are snake and flying serpent;
        they carry their wealth on the backs of male donkeys and their treasures
        on the humps of camels, to a people that cannot profit them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For Egyptians help with vanity and emptiness, therefore I have called
        this one \u201CRahab, they are sitting.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now go, write it on a tablet with them, and inscribe it on a scroll,
        that it may be for the time to come,  forever, forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For it is a people of rebellion, deceitful children, children who
        are not willing to hear the instruction of Yahweh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "who say to those who do see, \u201CYou must not see!\u201D and to
        the seers, \u201CYou must not see truth for us; speak smooth things to us,
        see illusions, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "turn aside from the way, turn aside from the path, put an end to
        the holy one of Israel from our face.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore the holy one of Israel says this: \u201CBecause you are
        rejecting this word and you trust in oppression and cunning  and you rely
        on it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'therefore this iniquity shall come for you like a breach about to
        fall, bulging out on a high wall that breaks suddenly, in an instant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he breaks it like a vessel of a potter breaks, that is crushed;
        he has no compassion, and no potsherd is found among its fragments to take
        fire from the hearth, or to skim water from the cistern.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For the Lord Yahweh, the holy one of Israel, said this: \u201CIn
        returning and rest you shall be saved; your strength shall be in quietness
        and in trust.\u201D But you were not willing, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and you said, \u201CNo! For we will flee on horses!\u201D Therefore
        you shall flee! And, \u201CWe will ride on swift horses!\u201D Therefore
        your pursuers shall be swift! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Yahweh Will Show Mercy'
      title: Yahweh Will Show Mercy
      number: 17
      content: 'One thousand because of a threat of one, because of a threat of five
        you shall flee, until you are left like a flagstaff on top of a mountain,
        and like a signal on a hill. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore Yahweh waits to be gracious to you, and therefore he will
        rise up to show you mercy, for Yahweh is a God of justice; blessed are all
        those who wait for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For people will live in Zion; in Jerusalem, you will surely not weep.
        Surely he will be gracious to you; when he hears the sound of your cry, he
        will answer you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the Lord will give you the bread of distress and the water of
        oppression, but your teachers will not hide themselves any longer. And your
        eyes shall see your teachers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And your ears shall hear a word from behind you, saying, \u201Cthis
        is the way; walk in it,\u201D when you go to your right and when you go to
        your left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And you will defile the plating of your silver idols and the covering
        of your gold image. You will scatter them like contaminated things;  you
        will say to it, \u201CFilth!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And he will give rain for your seed with which you sow the ground,
        and grain, the produce of the ground, and it will be rich and fertile.  On
        that day, your cattle will graze in broad pastures;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and the oxen and the donkeys that till the ground will eat fodder,
        sorrel that has been winnowed with shovel and pitchfork. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And there will be streams on every high mountain and elevated hill,
        watercourses of water, on a day of great slaughter, when towers fall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Judgment against Assyria'
      title: Judgment against Assyria
      number: 26
      content: 'And the light of the full moon will be like the light of the sun,
        and the light of the sun will be sevenfold, like the light of seven days,
        on the day when Yahweh binds up the breakage of his people, and he heals
        the wound of his blow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Look! The name of Yahweh comes from afar, burning with his anger
        and heaviness of cloud. His lips are full of indignation, and his tongue
        is like a devouring fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And his breath is like an overflowing river; it reaches up to the
        neck to shake the nations with the sieve of worthlessness; and a bridle that
        leads astray is on the jawbones of the peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You shall have a song as in the night when a holy festival is kept,
        and a gladness of heart like one who goes with the flute, to go to the mountain
        of Yahweh, to the rock of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Yahweh will cause the majesty of his voice to be heard, and he
        will cause the descent of his arm to be seen, in furious anger and a flame
        of devouring fire, with a cloudburst and a rainstorm and stones of hail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Indeed, Assyria will be shattered by the voice of Yahweh; he strikes
        with the rod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And every stroke of the staff of foundation that Yahweh lays will
        be on it with timbrels and lyres, and he will fight against it with battles
        of brandishing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'For Topheth has been prepared from yesterday; indeed, it is made
        ready for the king. He makes its pile of wood deep and wide; he makes fire
        and wood abundant.  The breath of Yahweh burns in it like a stream of sulfur. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Egyptians are No Help'
      title: The Egyptians are No Help
      number: 1
      content: 'Ah! Those who go down to Egypt for help! They rely on horses and
        trust in chariots because they are many, and in horsemen because they are
        very numerous, and they do not look to the holy one of Israel, and they do
        not consult Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And indeed, he is wise, and he brings disaster, and he does not remove
        his words, and he will rise against the house of evildoers and against the
        help of workers of iniquity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the Egyptians are human and not God, and their horses are flesh
        and not spirit. And Yahweh stretches out his hand, and the helper will stumble,
        and the one being helped will fall, and together all of them will come to
        an end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For Yahweh said this to me: \u201CAs which a lion growls and a young
        lion over its prey when a full group of shepherds is called against him,
        it is not terrified by their voice, and to their noise it does not respond,
        so Yahweh of hosts will come down to fight upon Mount Zion and upon its hill. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Like birds flying overhead, so Yahweh of hosts will protect Jerusalem;
        he will protect and deliver it; he will pass over and rescue it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Turn back to the one against whom the sons of Israel have made deep
        rebellion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For on that day, each one will reject his idols of silver and his
        idols of gold which your hands have made in sin for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Assyria shall fall by a sword not of a man, and a sword not of
        a human shall devour him; and he shall flee from the sword, and his young
        men shall be put to forced labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And his rock will pass over because of terror, and his officers will
        be terrified because of the flag,\u201D declares Yahweh, who has a fire in
        Zion and has a furnace in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Kingdom of Righteousness'
      title: The Kingdom of Righteousness
      number: 1
      content: 'See, a king will rule according to righteousness, and princes will
        rule according to justice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And each one will be like a hiding place from the wind and a covering
        from the rainstorm, like streams of water in a dry region, like the shade
        of a large rock in a weary land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the eyes of those who see will not gaze,  and the ears of those
        who hear will listen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the minds of the rash will understand knowledge,  and the tongues
        of stammerers will hasten to speak clearly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A fool will no longer be called noble, and a scoundrel will not be
        said to be eminent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For a fool speaks folly, and his mind does iniquity: to behave wickedly, 
        and to speak error concerning Yahweh, to leave the throat of the hungry empty,
        and he deprives the thirsty of drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And a scoundrel, his weapons are evil; he plans evil devices to ruin
        the poor with words of deception even when the speech of the needy is right. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Against the Carefree Women'
      title: Against the Carefree Women
      number: 8
      content: 'But the nobleman plans noble things, and he stands upon noble things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Women who are at ease, rise up; hear my voice! Carefree daughters,
        listen to my word! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In a year you will tremble, carefree ones, for the vintage will come
        to an end; the harvest will not come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Tremble, you who are at ease; tremble, carefree ones; strip, and
        strip yourself, and gird yourself on your loins,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'mourning over breasts, over fields of delight, over the fruitful
        vine, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'over the soil of my people. It goes up in thorns and briers,  indeed
        over all of the houses of joy in the jubilant city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the palace will be forsaken, the crowded city deserted; the hill
        and the watchtower will become a cave forever, the joy of wild asses, a pasture
        for flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Until a spirit is poured out on us from on high, and the wilderness
        becomes a fruitful field, and the fruitful field is reckoned as the forest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then justice will dwell in the wilderness, and righteousness will
        live in the fruitful field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the work of righteousness will be peace, and the work of righteousness,
        quietness and security forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And my people will dwell in a settlement of peace and in a dwelling
        place of security and in undisturbed resting places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And it hails when the forest comes down,  and the city will become
        low in humiliation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Happy are you who sow by all waters, who let the foot of the ox and
        the donkey go free. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh\u2019s Judgment and Help"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Judgment and Help"
      number: 1
      content: 'Ah, destroyer, and yourself not destroyed! And treacherous one, and
        no one has dealt treacherously with him!  When you cease destroying, you
        will be destroyed. When you stop dealing treacherously, one will deal treacherously
        with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yahweh, be gracious to us, we wait for you. Be our arm in the mornings,
        indeed our salvation in the time of trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'At the sound of tumult, peoples fled; because of your exaltation,
        nations scattered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And your spoil is gathered, as the gathering of the locust, as a
        swarm of locusts storming on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yahweh is exalted, for he dwells on high; he filled Zion with justice
        and righteousness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and he will be the security of your times, an abundance of salvation,
        wisdom, and knowledge. The fear of Yahweh is his treasure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Look! Their heroes cry out in the street; the messengers of peace
        weep bitterly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Highways are deserted; the traveler on the road ceases. One breaks
        a treaty, he rejects the cities,  he does not hold man in high regard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The land mourns; it languishes. Lebanon feels abashed; it withers.
        Sharon is like the desert, and Bashan and Carmel are losing their leaves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CNow I will arise,\u201D says Yahweh. \u201CNow I will lift
        myself up proudly; now I will raise myself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You conceive dry grass, you bring forth stubble; your breath is a
        fire; it will consume you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the peoples will be burning to lime\u2014 they are burned like
        thorns that have been cut down in the fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You who are far away, hear what I have done; and you who are near,
        know my might!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Sinners are afraid in Zion; trembling has seized the godless: \u201CWho
        of us can live with devouring fire? Who of us can live with everlasting consuming
        hearths?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He who walks in righteousness and speaks uprightness, who rejects
        the gain of extortion, who refuses a bribe, who stops up his ears from hearing
        bloodshed  and shuts his eyes from seeing evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'That one will live on the heights; the fortresses of rocks will be
        his refuge. His food will be given; his waters will endure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Your eyes will see the king in his beauty; they will see a distant
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Your mind will meditate on the terror: \u201CWhere is the one who
        counted? Where is the one who weighed out? Where is the one who counted the
        towers?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You will not see the insolent people, the people whose language is
        too obscure to understand,  whose stammering of tongue cannot be understood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Look on Zion, the city of our appointed festivals! Your eyes will
        see Jerusalem, an undisturbed settlement, a tent that is not moved.  No one
        will ever pull out its tent pegs, and none of its ropes will be torn in two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Rather, there Yahweh will be mighty for us, a place of rivers and
        broad streams,  a galley ship with oars cannot go in it, and a mighty ship
        cannot pass through it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For Yahweh is our judge; Yahweh is our lawgiver. Yahweh is our king;
        he is the one who will save us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Your riggings hang slack; they do not hold the base of their mast
        firm, they do not spread out the sail. Then the prey of spoil in abundance
        will be divided; the lame will take plunder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And no inhabitant will say, \u201CI am sick\u201D; the people who
        live in it, their iniquity will be taken away. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on the Nations'
      title: Judgment on the Nations
      number: 1
      content: 'Come near, nations, to hear; and peoples, listen attentively! Let
        the earth hear, and that which fills it; the world and all its offspring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the anger of Yahweh is against all the nations, and his wrath
        is against all their armies; he has put them under a ban, he has given them
        up for slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And their slain shall be cast out; as for their corpses, their stench
        shall go up. And the mountains shall melt with their blood, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and all the host of heaven shall rot. And the skies shall roll up
        like a scroll, and all their host shall wither like the withering of a leaf
        from a vine, or like the withering from a fig tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When my sword is drenched in the heavens, look! It will descend upon
        Edom, and upon the people of my ban, for judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Yahweh has a sword;  it is full of blood. It is covered with fat,
        with the blood of lambs and goats, with the fat of the kidneys of rams, for
        Yahweh has a sacrifice in Bozrah and a great slaughter in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And wild oxen shall go down with them, and steers with strong bulls.
        And their land shall be drenched with blood, and their soil shall be fattened
        with fat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For Yahweh has a day of vengeance,  a year of retribution for the
        strife of Zion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And its streams shall be changed to pitch and its soil to sulfur,
        and its land shall become like burning pitch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Night and day it shall not be quenched; its smoke shall go up forever.
        From generation to generation it shall be in ruins; forever and ever there
        will be no one who passes through her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the large bird and the hedgehog shall take possession of it,
        and the owl and the raven shall live in it. And he shall stretch the measuring
        line of confusion out over it, and the plumb line of emptiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Its nobles\u2014but no kingdom is there\u2014shall call, and all
        its princes shall be nothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And thorns shall go up her citadel fortress, weeds and thistle plants
        in her fortresses; and it shall be the settlement of jackals, green grass
        for the daughters of an ostrich. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And desert creatures shall meet with hyenas, and a goat-demon shall
        call to his neighbor; surely there Lilith shall repose, and she shall find
        a resting place for herself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'There the owl shall nest and lay and hatch and care for her chicks
        in her shadow; surely there the birds of prey shall be gathered, each one
        with her mate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Seek from the book of Yahweh and read;  none of these shall be missing;
        none shall miss her mate. For my mouth is the one that has commanded, and
        his spirit is the one that has gathered them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he is the one that has cast the lot for them, and his hand has
        apportioned it to them with the measuring line; they shall take possession
        of it forever, they shall live in it from generation to generation.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ransomed Return to Zion'
      title: The Ransomed Return to Zion
      number: 1
      content: 'Wilderness and dry land shall be glad,  and desert shall rejoice
        and blossom like the crocus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It shall blossom abundantly, and it shall rejoice indeed with rejoicing
        and exulting. The glory of Lebanon shall be given to it, the majesty of Carmel
        and Sharon. They are the ones who shall see the glory of Yahweh, the majesty
        of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Strengthen the weak hands and make the staggering knees firm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say to those who are hasty of heart, \u201CBe strong; you must not
        fear! Look! your God will come with vengeance, with divine retribution. 
        He is the one who will come and save you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the eyes of the blind shall be opened, and the ears of the deaf
        shall be opened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the lame shall leap like the deer, and the tongue of the dumb
        shall sing for joy, for waters shall break forth in the wilderness and streams
        in the desert. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the parched ground shall become a pool, and the thirsty ground
        springs of water. Her resting place is in a settlement of jackals; the grass
        shall become like reeds and rushes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And a highway shall be there, and a way, and it shall be called the
        way of holiness. The unclean shall not travel through it, but it is for them,
        he who walks on the way; and fools shall not wander about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'No lion shall be there, and no ferocious wild beast shall go up it.
        It shall not be found there, but the redeemed shall walk there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the ransomed of Yahweh shall return, and they shall come to Zion
        with rejoicing. And everlasting joy shall be on their head; joy and gladness
        shall overtake them, and sorrow and sighing shall flee. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sennacherib Threatens Jerusalem'
      title: Sennacherib Threatens Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'And this happened: In the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib
        king of Assyria went up against all the fortified cities of Judah, and he
        captured them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the king of Assyria sent Rabshakeh from Lachish to Jerusalem,
        to King Hezekiah, with a large army, and he stood by the conduit of the upper
        pool on the highway of the field of the washer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Eliakim son of Hilkiah, who was in charge of the palace, came
        out to him, and Shebna the secretary, and Joah son of Asaph, the reminder. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CNow say to Hezekiah, \u2018Thus
        says the great king, the king of Assyria: \u201CWhat is this confidence in
        which you trust? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I said, \u2018Only a word of lips! War has power and a plan!\u2019
        Now, in whom do you trust, that you have rebelled against me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Look, you trust in the staff of this broken reed, on Egypt, which
        if a man leans on it, goes into his hand and bores through it! Such is Pharaoh,
        king of Egypt, to all those who trust in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And if you say to me, \u2018We trust in Yahweh our God,\u2019 was
        it not he whose high places and altars Hezekiah removed? And he said to Judah
        and to Jerusalem, \u2018You shall bow down in the presence of this altar.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And now please make a wager with my master the king of Assyria, and
        I will give you two thousand horses, that is, if you are able put riders
        for yourself on them! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But how can you drive back one governor among the least of my master\u2019s
        servants, when you trust in Egypt for chariots and horsemen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And now was it without Yahweh that I have come up against this land
        to destroy it? Yahweh said to me, \u201CGo up against this land and destroy
        it!\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Eliakim, Shebna, and Joah said to Rabshakeh, \u201CPlease speak
        to your servants in Aramaic, for we can understand it, and you must not speak
        to us in Judean in the hearing of the people who are on the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Rabshakeh said, \u201CHas my master sent me to speak these words
        to your masters and you? Was it not for the people who sit on the wall, to
        eat their dung and drink their urine with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Rabshakeh stood and called in a great voice in Judean and said,
        \u201CHear the words of the great king, the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says the king: \u2018Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he
        will not be able to deliver you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And do not let Hezekiah make you rely on Yahweh, saying, \u201CSurely
        Yahweh will deliver us; this city will not be given into the hand of the
        king of Assyria!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "You must not listen to Hezekiah, for thus says the king of Assyria:
        \u201CMake a blessing with me, and come out to me, and each one will eat
        from his vine and from his fig tree and drink water from his cistern, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'until I come and take you to a land like your land, a land of grain
        and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "lest Hezekiah mislead you, saying, \u2018Yahweh will save us!\u2019
        Did the gods of the nations each save his land from the hand of the king
        of Assyria? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim?
        Indeed, have they delivered Samaria from my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Who are there among all the gods of these countries who have saved
        their land from my hand, that Yahweh should save Jerusalem from my hand?\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But they were silent and did not answer him a word, for the command
        of the king was, \u201CYou must not answer him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Eliakim son of Hilkiah, who was over the palace, Shebna the
        secretary, and Joah son of Asaph, the reminder, came to Hezekiah with torn
        garments and told him the words of Rabshakeh. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Consults Isaiah'
      title: Hezekiah Consults Isaiah
      number: 1
      content: 'And this happened: When King Hezekiah heard, he tore his garments,
        covered himself with sackcloth, and entered the temple of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he sent Eliakim, who was in charge of the palace, and Shebna
        the secretary, and the elders of the priests covered with sackcloth to Isaiah
        son of Amoz, the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CThus says Hezekiah: \u2018This day is
        a day of distress, rebuke, and disgrace, for children have come to the cervical
        opening, and there is no strength to give birth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Maybe Yahweh your God heard the words of Rabshakeh whom the king
        of Assyria, his master, has sent to taunt the living God, and he will rebuke
        the words that Yahweh your God hears. And you must lift up a prayer for the
        benefit of the remnant that is found.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Isaiah said to them, \u201CYou must say this to your master: \u2018Thus
        says Yahweh: \u201CYou must not be afraid because of the words that you have
        heard, with which the servants of the king of Assyria have blasphemed me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Look! I am about to put a spirit in him so that he shall hear a rumor
        and he shall return to his land, and I will cause him to fall by the sword
        in his land.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Rabshakeh returned and found the king of Assyria fighting against
        Libnah, for he had heard that he had left from Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now he heard concerning Tirhakah the king of Cush, saying, \u201CHe
        has set out to fight against you.\u201D When he heard it, he sent messengers
        to Hezekiah, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou shall say this to Hezekiah, king of Judah: \u2018Do not
        let your God in whom you trust in him deceive you by saying, \u201CJerusalem
        will not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Look! you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all lands
        to destroy them, and you\u2014shall you be delivered? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Did the gods of the nations that my predecessors destroyed deliver
        them\u2014Gozan, Haran, Rezeph, and the sons of Eden who were in Telassar? "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 13
      content: "Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king of the city
        of Sepharvaim, Hena, or Ivvah?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Hezekiah took the letter from the hand of the messengers, and
        he read it. Then he went up to the temple of Yahweh, and Hezekiah spread
        it out before the presence of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Hezekiah prayed to Yahweh, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CYahweh of hosts, God of Israel who is enthroned on the cherubim,
        you are the one, God by yourself, of all the kingdoms of the earth; you are
        the one who made the heavens and the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Yahweh, extend your ear and hear! Yahweh, open your eyes and see,
        and hear all the words of Sennacherib that he has sent to taunt the living
        God! '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Truly, Yahweh, the kings of Assyria have laid waste all the lands
        and their land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'to set their gods in the fire, for they were not gods, but the work
        of human hands, wood and stone, and they destroyed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: "20: God\u2019s Answer"
      title: "God\u2019s Answer"
      number: 20
      content: "So now, Yahweh, our God, save us from his hand so that all the kingdoms
        of the earth may know that you are Yahweh, you alone!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Isaiah son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, \u201CThus says
        Yahweh the God of Israel: \u2018Because you have prayed to me concerning
        Sennacherib, king of Assyria, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'this is the word that Yahweh has spoken concerning him: She shows
        contempt for you; she derides you, virgin daughter of Zion; she shakes her
        head behind you, daughter of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Whom have you taunted and blasphemed, and against whom have you raised
        up your voice and lifted your eyes upward? To the holy one of Israel! '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "By the hand of your servants you have taunted the Lord, and you have
        said, \u201CWith my many chariots,  I myself have gone up the height of the
        mountains, to the remote areas of Lebanon. And I cut off its tall cedars, 
        the choicest of its junipers. And I came to the height of its limit, the
        forest of its orchard.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I myself dug and drank waters, and I caused all the streams of Egypt
        to dry up by the sole of my feet.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Have you not heard from a long time ago? I have made it from days
        of primeval time, and I formed it. Now I have brought it about, and it is
        for fortified cities to collapse into heaps of destroyed stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And their inhabitants are weak;  they are dismayed, and they are
        ashamed; they have become like plants of the field, and like greens of grass,
        like grass on the roofs and a cultivated field before the standing grain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And I know your sitting down and your going out, and your coming
        in, and your raging against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Because you were enraged against me, and your noise has come up to
        my ears, I will put my hook in your nose and my bridle on your lips, and
        I will turn you back on the way by which you came. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And this shall be the sign for you: the eating of volunteer plants
        this year, and in the second year self-seeded plants, and in the third year
        sow, reap, plant vineyards, and eat their fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And the remnant of the house of Judah that remain shall grow roots
        downwards and make fruit upwards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For a remnant shall go out from Jerusalem and survivors from mountain
        Zion. The zeal of Yahweh of hosts will do this.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Therefore thus says Yahweh concerning the king of Assyria: \u2018He
        shall not come to this city, and he shall not shoot an arrow there, and he
        shall not meet it with a shield, and he shall not heap a siege ramp up against
        her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "He shall return by the way that he came, and he shall not come to
        this city,\u2019 declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: "35: Sennacherib\u2019s Defeat"
      title: "Sennacherib\u2019s Defeat"
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018And I will defend this city, to save it for my sake and for
        the sake of David, my servant.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And the angel of Yahweh set out and struck one hundred and eighty-five
        thousand in the camp of the Assyrians. When they rose in the morning, look!
        All of them were dead corpses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then Sennacherib king of Assyria left, went, and returned and lived
        at Nineveh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And this happened: he was bowing in worship in the house of Nisroch
        his god, and Adrammelech and Sharezer, his sons, struck him with the sword.
        And they themselves escaped to the land of Ararat, and Esar-haddon his son
        reigned as king in his place. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hezekiah\u2019s Illness"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Illness"
      number: 1
      content: "In those days, Hezekiah became sick to death, and Isaiah son of Amoz,
        the prophet, came to him and said to him, \u201CThus says Yahweh: \u2018Order
        your house, for you are about to die, and you shall not recover.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to Yahweh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and he said, \u201CO Yahweh, please remember how I have walked before
        your presence in faithfulness with a whole heart, and I have done the good
        in your eyes!\u201D And Hezekiah wept with great weeping. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the word of Yahweh came to Isaiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo and say to Hezekiah, \u2018Thus says Yahweh, the God of
        David your ancestor: \u201CI have heard your prayer; I have seen your tears.
        Look, I am going to add fifteen years to your days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And I will deliver you and this city from the hand of the king of
        Assyria, and I will defend this city.\u201D&nbsp;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And this is the sign to you from Yahweh, that Yahweh will do this
        thing that he has spoken: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Look! I will cause the shadow of the steps, which it had gone down
        on the steps of Ahaz with the sun, to turn backwards ten steps.\u201D And
        the sun turned back ten steps on the steps which it had gone down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A writing of Hezekiah, king of Judah, when he was sick and had recovered
        from his sickness: '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I was the one who said, \u201CI must go in the quiet of my days;
        I am summoned through the gates of Sheol for the rest of my years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I said, \u201CI shall not see Yah! Yah in the land of the living!
        I shall no more look at humankind among the inhabitants of the world. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'My dwelling place is pulled up and removed from me like the tent
        of my shepherd; I have rolled up my life like a weaver. He cuts me off from
        the thrum; from day to night you bring me to an end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I lie down until morning; like a lion, so he breaks all my bones;
        from day to night you bring me to an end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Like a horse or a crane, so I chirp; I moan like a dove. My eyes
        are weak toward the height. Lord, I have oppression; lend me support! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'What can I say? For he has spoken to me, and he himself has done
        it. I will walk slowly all my years because of the bitterness of my soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Lord, they live by them, and the life of my spirit belongs to all
        among them. And restore me to health and keep me alive! '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Look! Bitterness was bitter to me for peace. And you were the one
        who loved my life from the pit of destruction, for you have cast all my sins
        behind your back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For Sheol cannot praise you; death cannot praise you. Those who go
        down to the pit cannot hope for your faithfulness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The living, the living one praises you like me today; a father will
        make your faithfulness known to children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Yahweh, save me, and we will play my music on stringed instruments
        all the days of our lives at the temple of Yahweh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Isaiah said, \u201CLet them take a lump of figs, and let them
        rub it on the boil so that he may recover.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Hezekiah said, \u201CWhat is the sign that I shall go up to the
        temple of Yahweh?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Delegation from Babylon'
      title: The Delegation from Babylon
      number: 1
      content: 'At that time, Merodach-Baladan, son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he heard that he had been sick
        and recovered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Hezekiah rejoiced over them and showed them his house of aromatic
        gum, the silver, gold, spices, good oil, all the house of his weapons, and
        all that was found in his storehouses. There was nothing that Hezekiah had
        not shown them in his house or in all his dominion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah and said to him, \u201CWhat
        did these men say, and from where did they come to you?\u201D And Hezekiah
        answered, \u201CThey came to me from a distant country, from Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat have they seen in your house?\u201D And Hezekiah
        answered, \u201CThey have seen all that is in my house. There is nothing
        that I have not shown them in my storehouses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHear the word of Yahweh of hosts: "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018Look! days are coming, and all that is in your house and that
        which your ancestors have stored up to this day shall be carried off to Babylon.
        Nothing shall be left,\u2019 says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018And some of your sons who go out from you, whom you fathered,
        shall be taken, and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of the king of Babylon.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CThe word of Yahweh that you have
        spoken is good,\u201D for he thought, \u201CSurely there will be peace and
        security in my days.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Comfort for God\u2019s People"
      title: "Comfort for God\u2019s People"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CComfort; comfort my people,\u201D says your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak to the heart of Jerusalem, and call to her, that her
        compulsory labor is fulfilled, that her sin is paid for, that she has received
        from the hand of Yahweh double for all her sins.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "A voice is calling in the wilderness, \u201CClear the way of Yahweh!
        Make a highway smooth in the desert for our God! "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Every valley shall be lifted up, and every mountain and hill shall
        become low, And the rough ground shall be like a plain, and the rugged ground
        like a valley-plain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the glory of Yahweh shall be revealed, and all humankind together
        shall see it, for the mouth of Yahweh has spoken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A voice is saying, \u201CCall!\u201D And he said, \u201CWhat shall
        I call?\u201D All humankind are grass, and all his loyalty is like the flowers
        of the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Grass withers; the flower withers when the breath of Yahweh blows
        on it. Surely the people are grass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Grass withers; the flower withers, but the word of our God will stand
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Get yourself up to a high mountain, Zion, bringer of good news! Lift
        up your voice with strength, Jerusalem, bringer of good news! Lift it up;
        you must not fear! Say to the cities of Judah, \u201CHere is your God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Look! The Lord Yahweh comes with strength,  and his arm rules for
        him. Look! His reward is with him, and his recompense in his presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He will feed his flock like a shepherd; he will gather the lambs
        in his arm, and he will carry them in his bosom; he will lead those who nurse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Who has measured the waters in the hollow of his hand and marked
        off the heavens with a span, comprehended the dust of the earth in a third
        of a measure and weighed out the mountains in the scales, and the hills in
        a balance? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who has measured up the spirit of Yahweh or informed him as his counselor? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'With whom has he consulted, that he enlightened him  and taught him
        the path of justice, and taught him knowledge, and made the way of understanding
        known to him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Look! The nations are like a drop from a bucket, and they are counted
        like dust of the balances! Look! He weighs the islands like a thin covering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Lebanon is not enough to light a fire, and its animals not enough
        for a burnt offering. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All the nations are like nothing before him; they are counted by
        him as nothing and emptiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And to whom will you liken God? And to what likeness will you compare
        him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'A craftsman pours out the idol, and a goldsmith overlays it with
        gold, and he smelts chains of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The one who is too impoverished for a gift chooses wood that will
        not rot; he seeks a skillful artisan for himself to set up an image that
        will not be knocked over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Have you not known? Have you not heard? Has it not been told to you
        from the beginning?  Have you not understood from the foundation of the earth? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He is the one who sits above the circle of the earth, and its inhabitants
        are like grasshoppers; the one who stretches out the heavens like a veil
        and spreads them out like a tent to live in, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the one who brings princes to nothing; he makes rulers of the earth
        like nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Indeed, hardly are they planted; indeed, hardly are they sown; indeed,
        hardly has their shoot taken root in the earth when he blows on them and
        they wither, and the tempest carries them like stubble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CAnd to whom you will compare me, and am I equal?\u201D says
        the holy one. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Lift your eyes up on high, and see! Who created these? The one who
        brings out their host by number. He calls all them by name. Because he is
        great of power and mighty of power, no man is missing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Why do you say, Jacob, and you speak, Israel, \u201CMy way is hidden
        from Yahweh, and my judgment is passed over by my God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Have you not known, or have you not heard? Yahweh is the God of eternity,
        the creator of the ends of the earth! He is not faint, and he does not grow
        weary! There is no searching his understanding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He gives power to the weary, and he increases power for the powerless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Even young people will be faint and grow weary, and the young will
        stumble, exhausted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But those who wait for Yahweh shall renew their strength. They shall
        go up with wings like eagles; they shall run and not grow weary; they shall
        walk and not be faint. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Helps Israel'
      title: God Helps Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Listen to me in silence, coastlands, and let nations renew their
        strength. Let them approach, then let them speak; let us draw near together
        for judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Who has roused salvation from the east, summoned him to his foot,
        gives nations in his presence,  and subjugates kings? He makes them like
        the dust with his sword, like scattered stubble with his bow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He pursues them and passes on in peace; he does not enter the path
        with his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Who has accomplished and done this, calling the generations from
        the beginning?  I, Yahweh, am first; and I am the one with the last. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The coastlands have seen and are afraid; the ends of the earth tremble.
        They have drawn near, and they have come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Each one helps his neighbor; he says to his brother, \u201CTake courage!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the artisan encourages the goldsmith,  the one who makes smooth
        with the hammer encourages the one who strikes the anvil, saying of the soldering,
        \u201CIt is good!\u201D And they strengthen it with nails so it cannot be
        knocked over. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But you, Israel, my servant, Jacob, whom I have chosen, you, the
        offspring of Abraham my friend,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "you whom I grasped from the ends of the earth and called from its
        remotest parts and told, \u201CYou are my servant; I have chosen you and
        I have not rejected you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You must not fear, for I am with you; you must not be afraid, for
        I am your God. I will strengthen you, indeed I will help you, indeed I will
        take hold of you with the right hand of my salvation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Look! All those who are angry with you shall be ashamed and humiliated;
        your opponents shall be like nothing and shall become lost. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You shall seek them, but you shall not find them; your opponents
        shall be like nothing, and the men of your war like nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I, Yahweh your God, am grasping your right hand; it is I who
        say to you, \u201CYou must not fear; I myself, I will help you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "You must not fear, O worm of Jacob; people of Israel, I myself, I
        will help you,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand your redeemer is the holy
        one of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Look! I will make you into a new sharp threshing sledge, with sharp
        edges. You shall thresh and crush the mountains, and you shall make the hills
        like chaff. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You shall winnow them and the wind shall carry them, and the tempest
        shall scatter them. And you yourself shall rejoice in Yahweh; you shall boast
        in the holy one of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The poor and the needy are seeking water and there is none; their
        tongue is dried up with thirst. I, Yahweh, will answer them; I, the God of
        Israel, will not forsake them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will open rivers on the barren heights and fountains in the midst
        of the valleys. I will make the wilderness like a pool of water and the land
        of dryness like springs of water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will put the cedar, acacia, myrtle, and olive oil tree in the wilderness;
        I will set the cypress, elm, and box tree together in the desert '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "so that they may see and know, and take to heart and understand together
        that the hand of Yahweh has done this, and the holy one of Israel has created
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CPresent your legal case,\u201D says Yahweh. \u201CBring your
        evidence,\u201D says the king of Jacob. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Let them bring them, and let them tell us what will happen. Tell
        us what the former things are so that we may take them to our heart and know
        their outcome.  Declare to us the things to come; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'tell us the things coming hereafter,  that we may know that you are
        gods. Indeed, do good or do evil, that we may be afraid and see together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Look! you are nothing, and your work is something worthless; whoever
        chooses you is an abomination. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I stirred up one from the north, and he has come from the rising
        of the sun. He shall call on my name, and he shall come on officials as on
        mortar, and as the potter treads clay. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Who declared it from the beginning so that we might know, and beforehand
        so that we might say, \u201CHe is right!\u201D  Indeed, there was no one
        who declared it; Indeed, there was no one who proclaimed it. Indeed there
        was no one who heard your words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'First to Zion, look! Look at them! And I give a herald of good tidings
        to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But I look and there is no man, and I look among these and there
        is no counselor, that I might ask them and they might answer a word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Look! All of them are deception; their works are nothing; their images
        are wind and emptiness. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Mission of Yahweh\u2019s Servant"
      title: "The Mission of Yahweh\u2019s Servant"
      number: 1
      content: 'Look! here is my servant; I hold him, my chosen one, in whom my soul
        delights. I have put my spirit on him; he will bring justice forth to the
        nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He will not cry out and lift up and make his voice heard in the street. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He will not break a broken reed, and he not will extinguish a dim
        wick. He will bring justice forth in faithfulness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He will not grow faint, and he will not be broken until he has established
        justice in the earth. And the coastlands wait for his teaching. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus says the God, Yahweh, who created the heavens and stretched
        them out, who spread out the earth and its offspring, who gives breath to
        the people upon it and spirit to those who walk in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI am Yahweh; I have called you in righteousness, and I have
        grasped your hand and watched over you; and I have given you as a covenant
        of the people, as a light of the nations, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'to open the blind eyes, to bring the prisoner out from the dungeon,
        those who sit in darkness from the house of imprisonment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I am Yahweh; that is my name, and I do not give my glory to another,
        nor my praise to the idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: A Song of Praise to Yahweh'
      title: A Song of Praise to Yahweh
      number: 9
      content: "Look! the former things have come, and I declare new things. I announce
        them to you before they sprout up.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Sing a new song to Yahweh; praise him from the end of the earth,
        you who go down to the sea and that which fills it, the coastlands and their
        inhabitants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let the desert and its towns lift up their voice, the villages that
        Kedar inhabits. Let the inhabitants of Sela sing for joy; let them shout
        loudly from the top of the mountains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let them give glory to Yahweh and declare his praise in the coastlands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yahweh goes forth like a mighty warrior; he stirs up zeal like a
        man of war. He raises the war cry, indeed he raises the battle shout; he
        prevails against his foes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have been silent for a long time; I have kept silent; I have restrained
        myself like one giving birth; I will moan, pant, and gasp together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will cause mountains and hills to dry up, and I will cause all
        their herbage to wither; and I will make rivers like islands, and I will
        cause pools to dry up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And I will lead the blind by a road they do not know; I will cause
        them to tread on paths they have not known. I will make darkness in their
        presence into light and rough places into level ground. These are the things
        I will do, and I will not forsake them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Blind and Deaf Israel'
      title: Blind and Deaf Israel
      number: 17
      content: "They shall turn back; they shall be greatly ashamed,  those who trust
        in an image, who say to a cast image, \u201CYou are our gods.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Deaf people, listen! And blind people, look to see! '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Who is blind but my servant or deaf like my messenger whom I sent?
        Who is blind like the one who is repaid or blind like the servant of Yahweh? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You see many things, but you do not observe. His ears are open, but
        he does not hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Yahweh was willing for the sake of his righteousness; he showed his
        teaching to be great and proved it to be glorious. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But this is a people plundered and looted; all of them are trapped
        in holes, and they are kept hidden in houses of imprisonment. They have become
        like plunder, and there is no one who saves; like booty, and there is no
        one who says, \u201CRestore!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Who among you will heed this, will listen attentively and listen,
        for the time to come?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Who gave Jacob to a plunderer  and Israel to those who plunder? Was
        it not Yahweh, against whom we have sinned? And they were not willing to
        walk in his ways, and they would not obey his law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So he poured the wrath of his anger upon him and the strength of
        war. And it set him afire all around, but he did not understand;  and it
        burned him, but he did not take it to heart. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Restorer of Israel'
      title: The Restorer of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "But now thus says Yahweh, he who created you, Jacob, and he who formed
        you, Israel: \u201CYou must not fear, for I have redeemed you. I have called
        you by your name; you are mine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When you pass through the waters, I will be with you, and through
        the rivers, they shall not flow over you. When you walk through fire, you
        shall not be burned, and the flame shall not scorch you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I am Yahweh, your God, the holy one of Israel, your savior. I
        give you Egypt as ransom, Cush and Seba in place of you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because you are precious in my eyes, you are honored, and I myself
        love you, and I give people in place of you, and nations in place of your
        life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You must not fear, for I am with you. I will bring your offspring
        from the east, and I will gather you from the west. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will say to the north, \u2018Give!\u2019 and to the south, \u2018You
        must not withhold!\u2019 Bring my sons from far away, and my daughters from
        the end of the earth\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "everyone who is called by my name, and whom I created for my glory,
        whom I formed, indeed whom I made.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Bring out the people blind yet with eyes, and deaf, though they have
        ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Let all the nations gather together, and let the peoples assemble.
        Who among them has declared this, and declared the former things to us? Let
        them bring their witnesses, that they may be in the right, and let them hear
        and say, \u201CIt is true!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou are my witnesses,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand my servant
        whom I have chosen so that you may know and believe in me and understand
        that I am he. No god was formed before me, and none shall be after me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I myself am Yahweh, and there is no savior besides me! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I myself declared and saved, and I proclaimed. And there was no strange
        god among you. And you are my witnesses,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cand
        I am God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Yahweh Rescues His People'
      title: Yahweh Rescues His People
      number: 13
      content: "Indeed, from this day I am the one, and no one can deliver from my
        hand. I perform, and who can cancel it?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, your redeemer, the holy one of Israel: \u201CFor
        your sake I will send to Babylon, and I will cause all of them to fall down
        as fugitives, and the Chaldeans, their rejoicing on the ships. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I am Yahweh, your holy one, the creator of Israel, your king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Thus says Yahweh, who makes a way in the sea and a path in the mighty
        waters, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'who brings out chariot and horse, army and mighty one. Together they
        lie down; they cannot rise. They are extinguished, quenched like a wick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou must not remember the former things, and you not must consider
        the former things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Look! I am about to do a new thing! Now it sprouts! Do you not perceive
        it? Indeed, I will make a way in the wilderness, rivers in the desert. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The animals of the field will honor me, jackals and daughters of
        the ostrich, for I give water in the wilderness, rivers in the desert, to
        give a drink to my chosen people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'this people whom I formed for myself, so they might make known my
        praise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But you did not call me, Jacob; for you have become weary of me,
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You have not brought me your sheep for a burnt offering nor honored
        me with your sacrifice. I have not made you serve with offerings,  nor have
        I made you weary with frankincense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have not bought me spice reed with money or satisfied me with
        the fat of sacrifices. But you have burdened me with your sins; you have
        made me weary with your iniquities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I, I am the one who blots out your transgressions for my sake, and
        I will not remember your sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Take me to court; let us enter into judgment together. You, make
        an account so that you may be in the right. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Your first ancestor sinned, and your representatives transgressed
        against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And I profaned the princes of the sanctuary, and I gave Jacob to
        destruction, and Israel to reviling. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Blesses Chosen Israel'
      title: Yahweh Blesses Chosen Israel
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CBut now hear, Jacob my servant, and Israel, whom I have chosen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Thus says Yahweh, who made you, and who formed you in the womb and
        will help you: you must not fear, my servant Jacob, and Jeshurun whom I have
        chosen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I will pour out water on a thirsty land and streams on dry ground.
        I will pour my spirit out on your descendants  and my blessing on your offspring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they shall sprout among the grass like willows by a watercourse
        of water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Yahweh the Only God'
      title: Yahweh the Only God
      number: 5
      content: "This one will say, \u2018I belong to Yahweh!\u2019 And that one will
        be called by the name of Jacob, and another will write on his hand \u2018Yahweh\u2019s\u2019
        and take the name of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, the king of Israel, and its redeemer, Yahweh of
        hosts: \u201CI am the first, and I am the last, and there is no god besides
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And who is like me? Let him proclaim it! And let him declare it and
        set it in order for me since I established an eternal people and things that
        are to come, and let them tell them the things that are coming. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Idolatry Is Ridiculous'
      title: Idolatry Is Ridiculous
      number: 8
      content: "You must not tremble,  and you must not be paralyzed with fear. Have
        I not made you hear from of old  and declared it, and you are my witnesses?
        Is there a god besides me? And there is no rock! I know none!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All those who form an idol are nothing, and their delightful things
        do not profit. And their witnesses do not see or know, so they will be ashamed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who would form a god and cast an image of which he cannot profit? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Look! all his companions shall be ashamed, and the artisans are human!
        Let all of them assemble; let them stand up. They shall tremble;  they shall
        be ashamed together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The ironsmith works in the coals with his tool and forms it with
        hammers. And he makes it with his strong arm;  indeed, he becomes hungry,
        and he lacks strength; he does not drink water, and he is faint. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The woodworker stretches out a line; he makes an outline of it with
        a marker. He makes it with a knife and makes an outline of it with a compass.
        He makes it like the image of a man, like the beauty of a human, to dwell
        in a temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Cutting down cedars for himself, he chooses a holm tree and an oak,
        and he lets it grow strong for him among the trees of the forest. He plants
        a cedar, and the rain makes it grow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And it becomes fuel for a human,  and he takes some of it and grows
        warm; also, he kindles a fire and bakes bread. Also, he makes a god and bows
        in worship; he makes himself an image and bows down to it! '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He burns half of it in the fire; he eats meat over half of it; he
        roasts a roast and is satisfied. Also he grows warm and says, \u201CAh! I
        am warm! I see the fire!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he makes the remainder of it into a god! He bows down to his
        idol, and he bows in worship and prays to him, and he says, \u201CSave me,
        for you are my god!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They do not know, and they do not understand, for their eyes are
        besmeared so that they cannot see,  their minds so that they have no insight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And no one takes it to heart, and there is no knowledge and no understanding
        to say, \u201CI burned half of it in the fire and also I baked bread on its
        coals; I roasted meat, and I have eaten. And I shall make the rest of it
        into an abomination! I shall bow down to a block of wood!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Yahweh Remembers Israel'
      title: Yahweh Remembers Israel
      number: 20
      content: "He feeds on ashes; a deceived mind misleads him. And he cannot save
        himself, and he cannot say, \u201CIs this not an illusion in my right hand?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Remember these things, Jacob, and Israel, for you are my servant:
        I formed you; you are my servant; Israel, you will not be forgotten by me! '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I have wiped your transgressions out like a cloud and your sins like
        mist. Return to me, for I have redeemed you! '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Jerusalem Restored through Cyrus'
      title: Jerusalem Restored through Cyrus
      number: 23
      content: 'Sing for joy, heavens, for Yahweh has done it! Shout, depths of the
        earth! Break forth, mountains, in rejoicing, forest and every tree in it,
        for Yahweh has redeemed Jacob, and he will show his glory in Israel! '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, your redeemer, and he who formed you in the womb:
        \u201CI am Yahweh, who made everything, who stretched out the heavens alone,
        who spread out the earth\u2014who was with me?\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'who frustrates the signs of oracle priests and makes a fool of diviners,
        who drives the wise men back and makes their knowledge foolish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "who keeps the word of his servant and carries out the plan of his
        messengers, who says of Jerusalem, \u2018It shall be inhabited,\u2019 and
        of the cities of Judah, \u2018They shall be rebuilt, and I will restore its
        ruins\u2019; "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "who says to the deep, \u2018Dry up! And I will cause your rivers
        to dry up\u2019; "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "who says of Cyrus, \u2018My shepherd,\u2019 and he shall carry out
        all my wishes; and saying of Jerusalem, \u2018It shall be rebuilt,\u2019
        and the temple, \u2018It shall be founded.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Thus says Yahweh to his anointed one, to Cyrus, whose right hand
        I have grasped to subjugate nations before him, and I uncover the loins of
        kings to open doors before him, and the gates shall not be shut: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI myself will go before you, and I will level the mountains. 
        I will break the doors of bronze and cut throughthe bars of iron. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And I will give you the treasures of darkness and treasures of secret
        places so that you may know that I am Yahweh, the one who calls you by your
        name, the God of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for the sake of my servant Jacob, and Israel my chosen one. And I
        call you by your name; I give you a name of honor, though you do not know
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I am Yahweh, and there is none besides me; besides me there is no
        god. I gird you though you do not know me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'so that they may know from the rising of the sun and from the west
        that there is none besides me; I am Yahweh and there is none besides me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I form light and I create darkness; I make peace and I create evil;
        I am Yahweh; I do all these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Trickle, O heavens, from above, and let clouds trickle with righteousness;
        let the earth open so that salvation may be fruitful, and let it cause righteousness
        to sprout along with it.  I myself, Yahweh, have created it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Woe to the one who strives with his maker,  a potsherd among potsherds
        of earth! Does the clay say to the one who fashions it, \u2018What are you
        making?\u2019 and \u2018Your work has no hands\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Woe to the one who says to a father, \u2018What you are begetting?\u2019
        or to a woman, \u2018With what are you in labor?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, the holy one of Israel, and its maker:  \u201CAsk
        me of the things to come about my children, and you command me about the
        work of my hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I myself made the earth, and I created humankind upon it. I, my hands,
        stretched out the heavens, and I commanded all their host. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Yahweh the Only Savior'
      title: Yahweh the Only Savior
      number: 13
      content: "I myself have stirred him up in righteousness, and I will make all
        his paths smooth. He himself shall build my city, and he shall set my exiles
        free, not for price or a gift,\u201D says Yahweh of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CThe acquisition of Egypt and the merchandise
        of Cush and the Sabeans, tall men, shall pass over to you; they shall be
        yours, and they shall walk behind you. They shall pass over in chains, and
        they shall bow down to you; they will pray to you: \u2018Surely God is with
        you, and there is no other. Besides him there is no God.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Surely you are a God who keeps yourself hidden, God of Israel, the
        savior. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'All of them are ashamed and indeed humiliated; the craftsmen of idols
        go together in insult. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Israel is saved by Yahweh with everlasting salvation; you shall not
        be ashamed, and you shall not be humiliated to all eternity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, who created the heavens, he is God, who formed
        the earth and who made it. He himself established it; he did not create it
        as emptiness\u2014 he formed it for inhabiting. \u201CI am Yahweh and there
        is none besides me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I have spoken not in secrecy, in a place, a land, of darkness, I
        have not said to the descendants of Jacob, \u2018Seek me in vain!\u2019 
        I, Yahweh, am speaking righteousness, declaring uprightness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Assemble and come; draw near together, survivors of the nations!
        They do not know, those who carry their wooden idols  and pray to a god who
        cannot save. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Declare and present your case, also let them consult together! Who
        made this known from former times,  declared it from of old?  Was it not
        I, Yahweh? And there is no other god besides me, a righteous God besides
        me, and no savior besides me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Turn to me and be saved, all the ends of the earth, for I am God
        and there is none besides me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I have sworn by myself; a word that shall not return has gone forth
        from my mouth in righteousness: \u2018Every knee shall kneel down to me;
        every tongue shall swear.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Only in Yahweh,\u2019 one shall say to me, \u2018are righteousness
        and strength.\u2019 He shall come to him, and all those who were angry with
        him shall be ashamed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "In Yahweh all the offspring of Israel shall be in the right, and
        they shall boast.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Babylon\u2019s Idols"
      title: "Babylon\u2019s Idols"
      number: 1
      content: 'Bel bows down; Nebo is stooping. Their idols are on animals and on
        cattle; your cargo is carried as a burden on weary animals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They stoop; they bow down together. They are not able to save the
        burden, but they themselves go in captivity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CListen to me, house of Jacob, and all the remnant of the house
        of Israel who have been carried from the belly, who have been carried from
        the womb: "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Even to your old age I am he; even to your advanced age I myself
        will support you. I myself have made you, and I myself will carry you, and
        I myself will support you, and I will save you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'To whom will you liken me, and count as equal, and compare with me,
        as though we were alike? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Those who lavish gold from the purse and weigh out silver in the
        balance scales; hire a goldsmith  and he makes him a god; they bow down,
        indeed they bow in worship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They carry it on their shoulder; they support it and they set it
        in its place, and it stands in position. It cannot be removed from its place;
        even when he cries out to it, it does not answer. It does not save him from
        his trouble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Remember this and pluck up courage! Call to mind, you transgressors! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Remember the former things from a long time ago,  for I am God and
        there is none besides me, God and there is none like me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "who from the beginning declares the end, and from before, things
        that have not been done, who says, \u2018My plan shall stand,\u2019 and,
        \u2018I will accomplish all my wishes,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'who calls a bird of prey from the east, the man of his plan from
        a country from afar. Indeed I have spoken; indeed I will bring it to being.
        I have formed it; indeed I will do it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Listen to me, strong of heart, far from righteousness! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I bring my righteousness near; it is not far. And my salvation will
        not delay; and I will put salvation in Zion, for Israel my glory.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Babylon\u2019s Fall"
      title: "Babylon\u2019s Fall"
      number: 1
      content: 'Come down and sit on the dust, virgin daughter of Babylon! Sit on
        the ground without a throne, daughter of Chaldea! For they shall no longer
        call you tender and delicate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Take the pair of mill stones and grind flour! Uncover your veil,
        strip off your skirt, uncover your thigh, pass through the rivers! '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Your nakedness shall be exposed; indeed, your shame shall become
        visible. I will take vengeance and I will not spare a person. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Our redeemer, Yahweh of hosts is his name, the holy one of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Sit silently and go into the darkness, daughter of Chaldea, for they
        shall no longer call you mistress of kingdoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I was angry with my people; I profaned my inheritance, and I gave
        them into your hand. You did not give them mercy; on the aged you made your
        yoke very heavy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And you said, \u201CI shall be an eternal mistress forever!\u201D
        You did not set these things upon your heart; you did not remember its end. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore now hear this, luxuriant one who sits in security, who
        says in her heart, \u201CI am, and besides me there is no one. I shall not
        sit as a widow, and I shall not know the loss of children.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And these two shall come to you in a moment, in one day: the loss
        of children and widowhood shall come on you completely,  in spite of your
        many sorceries, in spite of the power of your great enchantments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And you felt secure in your wickedness; you said, \u201CNo one sees
        me.\u201D Your wisdom and your knowledge led you astray, and you said in
        your heart, \u201CI am, and besides me there is no one.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And evil shall come upon you, you will not know; it will be on the
        lookout for her. And disaster shall fall upon you; you will not be able to
        avert it. And ruin shall come on you suddenly; you do not know. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Stand, now, in your enchantments, and in your many sorceries with
        which you have labored from your youth. Perhaps you may be able to benefit;
        perhaps you may scare away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You struggle with your many consultations;  let them stand, now,
        and save you\u2014 those who see the stars, divide the celestial sphere, 
        who inform by new moons\u2014 from those things that are coming upon you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Look! They are like stubble; the fire burns them completely. They
        cannot deliver themselves from the power of the flame; there is no coal for
        warming oneself,  no fire before which to sit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So are to you those with whom you have labored, your traders from
        your youth. They wander, each to his side; there is no one who can save you. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Refines Stubborn Israel'
      title: Yahweh Refines Stubborn Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Hear this, house of Jacob, who are called by the name of Israel and
        came out from the waters of Judah, who swear by the name of Yahweh, and invoke
        the God of Israel, but not in truth and not in righteousness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For they call themselves after the holy city,  and they lean on the
        God of Israel\u2014 Yahweh of hosts is his name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI declared the former things from of old,  and they went out
        from my mouth. And I announced them suddenly; I acted, and they came to pass, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'because I know that you are obstinate, and your neck an iron sinew,
        and your forehead bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I declared them to you from of old; I announced them to you before
        they came to pass so that you would not say, \u2018My idol did them, and
        my image and my cast image commanded them.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You have heard; see it all. And will you not declare it? I announce
        new things to you from this time and hidden things that you have not known. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now they are created, and not from of old,  and before today, and
        you have not heard them so that you could not say, \u201CLook! I knew them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Neither have you heard, nor have you known, nor from of old has your
        ear been opened. For I knew you would deal treacherously, very treacherously,
        and you are called a rebel from the womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the sake of my name I refrain from my anger, and for my praise
        I restrain it for you so as not to cut you off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Look! I have refined you, but not like silver; I have chosen you
        in the furnace of misery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Yahweh Frees Israel'
      title: Yahweh Frees Israel
      number: 11
      content: "For my own sake, for my own sake I do it; for why should it be defiled?
        And I will not give my glory to another.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CListen to me, Jacob, and Israel, whom I called:  I am he. I
        am the first; also I am the last. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Indeed, my hand founded the earth, and my right hand spread out the
        heavens; when I summon them, they stand in position together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Assemble, all of you, and hear! Who among them declared these things?
        Yahweh loves him; he shall perform his wish against Babylon and his arm against
        the Chaldeans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I, I myself, I have spoken! Indeed, I have called him. I have brought
        him, and he will be successful in his way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Draw near to me; hear this! I have not spoken in secrecy from the
        beginning;  from the time it came to be, there I have been; And now the Lord
        Yahweh has sent me and his Spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, your redeemer, the holy one of Israel: \u201CI
        am Yahweh your God, who teaches you to profit, leads you in the way you should
        go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'O that you had listened attentively to my commandments! Then your
        prosperity would have been like a river, and your righteousness like the
        waves of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And your offspring would have been like the sand, and the descendants
        of your body like its grains.  It would not be cut off, and its name would
        not be destroyed from my presence.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Go out from Babylon! Flee from Chaldea! Proclaim it with a shout
        of rejoicing; proclaim this! Send it forth to the end of the earth; say,
        \u201CYahweh has redeemed his servant Jacob!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when he led them through the deserts, they were not thirsty;
        he made water flow from the rock for them, and he split the rock, and the
        water gushed out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThere is no peace,\u201D says Yahweh, \u201Cfor the wicked.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh\u2019s Servant Brings Salvation"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Servant Brings Salvation"
      number: 1
      content: 'Listen to me, coastlands, and listen attentively, peoples from far
        away! Yahweh called me from the womb; from the body of my mother he made
        my name known. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he made my mouth like a sharp sword; he hid me in the shadow
        of his hand, and he made me like an sharpened arrow; he hid me in his quiver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CYou are my servant, Israel, in whom I will
        show my glory.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But I myself said, \u201CI have labored in vain; I have used up my
        strength for nothing and vanity! Nevertheless, my justice is with Yahweh,
        and my reward is with my God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And now Yahweh says, who formed me from the womb as a servant for
        him, to bring Jacob back to him, and that Israel might not be gathered, for
        I am honored in the eyes of Yahweh, and my God has become my strength. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he says, \u201CIt is trivial for you to be a servant for me,
        to raise up the tribes of Jacob and to bring back the preserved of Israel.
        I will give you as a light to the nations, to be my salvation to the end
        of the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Yahweh Restores the Afflicted'
      title: Yahweh Restores the Afflicted
      number: 7
      content: "Thus says Yahweh, the redeemer of Israel, his holy one, to the one
        who despises life, to the one who abhors the nation, to the slave of rulers:
        \u201CKings shall see and stand up; princes, and they shall bow down, for
        the sake of Yahweh, who is faithful, the holy one of Israel, and he has chosen
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CI have answered you in a time of favor, and
        helped you on a day of salvation, and watched over you, and given you as
        a covenant of the people, to raise up the land, to give the desolate hereditary
        property as an inheritance, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "saying to the prisoners, \u201CCome out!\u201D to those who are in
        darkness, \u201CShow yourselves!\u201D they shall feed along the ways, and
        their pasturage shall be on all the barren heights. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They shall not be hungry or thirsty, and heat and sun shall not strike
        them, for he who takes pity on them will lead them, and he will guide them
        to springs of water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I will make all my mountains like a road, and my highways shall
        lead up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Look! These shall come from afar, And look! These from the north
        and from the west and these from the land of Sinim.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Yahweh Remembers Zion'
      title: Yahweh Remembers Zion
      number: 13
      content: 'Sing for joy, heavens, and rejoice, earth! Mountains must break forth
        in rejoicing! For Yahweh has comforted his people, and he will take pity
        on his afflicted ones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Zion said, \u201CYahweh has forsaken me, and the Lord has forgotten
        me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Can a woman forget her suckling, refrain from having compassion on
        the child of her womb? Indeed, these may forget, but I, I will not forget
        you! '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Look, I have inscribed you on the palms of my hands; your walls are
        continually before me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Your children hasten; your destroyers and those who laid you waste
        depart from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Lift your eyes up all around and see; all of them gather; they come
        to you. As surely as I live,  declares Yahweh, surely you shall put on all
        of them like an ornament, and you shall bind them on like a bride. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Surely your sites of ruins and desolate places and land of ruins, 
        surely now you will be too cramped for your inhabitants,  and those who engulfed
        you will be far away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Yet the children born when you were bereaved will say in your hearing, 
        \u201CThe place is too cramped for me; make room for me so that I can dwell.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you will say in your heart, \u201CWho has borne me these?\u201D
        And, \u201CI was bereaved and barren, exiled and thrust away; so who raised
        these? Look at me! I was left alone; where have these come from?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says the Lord Yahweh: \u201CLook! I will lift my hand up to
        the nations, and I will raise my signal to the peoples, and they shall bring
        your sons in their bosom, and your daughters shall be carried on their shoulders.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And kings shall be your guardians,  and their queens your nurses.
        They shall bow down, faces to the ground, to you, and they will lick up the
        dust of your feet. Then you will know that I am Yahweh; those who await me
        shall not be ashamed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Can war-booty be taken from the mighty? or can a captive of a righteous
        person be rescued? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But thus says Yahweh: \u201CIndeed a captive of the mighty shall
        be taken, and the war-booty of the tyrant shall be rescued, for I myself
        will dispute with your opponent, and I myself will save your children. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And I will feed your oppressors their own flesh, and they shall be
        drunk with their blood as with wine. Then all flesh shall know that I am
        Yahweh, your savior and redeemer, the strong one of Jacob.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: " Thus says Yahweh: \u201CWhere is this divorce document of your mother\u2019s
        divorce, with which I dismissed her? or to whom of my creditors did I sell
        you? Look! you were sold because of your sin, and your mother was dismissed
        because of your transgressions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Why was there no man when I came, no one who answered when I called?
        Do I lack the strength to save?  Or is there no power in me to deliver? Look!
        by my rebuke I dry up the sea; I make the rivers a desert; their fish stink
        because there is no water, and they die because of thirst. '
      comments: []
    - name: "3: The Servant\u2019s Vindication"
      title: "The Servant\u2019s Vindication"
      number: 3
      content: "I clothe the heavens with darkness, and I make their covering sackcloth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord Yahweh has given me the tongue of a pupil, to know how to
        help the weary with a word. He awakens morning by morning,  awakens an ear
        for me to listen as do the pupils. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord Yahweh has opened an ear for me, and I, I was not rebellious.
        I did not turn backwards; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I gave my back to those who struck me, and my cheeks to those who
        pulled out my beard;  I did not hide my face from insults and spittle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the Lord Yahweh helps me, therefore I have not been put to shame;
        therefore I have set my face like flint. And I know that I shall not be ashamed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'he who obtains rights for me is near. Who will contend with me? Let
        us stand together. Who is the master of my judgment? Let him approach me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Look! The Lord Yahweh helps me. Who is the one who will declare me
        guilty? Look! All of them will be worn out like a garment; the moth will
        eat them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who among you is in fear of Yahweh, obeys the voice of his servant?
        Who walks in darkness and has no light, trusts in the name of Yahweh and
        depends on his God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Look! All of you are kindlers of fire, who gird yourselves with flaming
        arrows. Walk in the light of your fire, and among the flaming arrows you
        have kindled! You shall have this from my hand: you shall lie down in a place
        of torment. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Comforts Zion'
      title: Yahweh Comforts Zion
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CListen to me, you who pursue righteousness, who seek Yahweh.
        Look to the rock from which you were hewn, and to the excavation of the pit
        from which you were quarried. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Look to Abraham your father, and to Sarah; she brought you forth.
        For I called him alone,  but I blessed him and made him numerous.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For Yahweh will comfort Zion; he will comfort all its sites of ruins.
        And he will make its wilderness like Eden, and its desert like the garden
        of Yahweh. Joy and gladness will be found in it, thanksgiving and the sound
        of song. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CListen attentively to me, my people, and my nation, listen
        to me! For a teaching will go out from me, and I will cause my justice to
        rest for a light to the peoples. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My righteousness is near; my salvation has gone out, and my arms
        will judge the peoples. The coastlands wait for me, and for my arm they wait. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Lift up your eyes to the heavens and look to the earth beneath, for
        the heavens will be torn to pieces like smoke, and the earth will be worn
        out like a garment, and those who inhabit her will die like gnats. But my
        salvation will be forever, and my righteousness will not be broken to pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Listen to me, you who know righteousness, people who have my teaching
        in their heart; you must not fear the reproach of men, or be terrified because
        of their abuse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For a moth will eat them like garments; a moth will devour them like
        wool, but my righteousness will be forever, and my salvation for generation
        after generation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Awake! Awake; put on strength, O arm of Yahweh! Awake as in days
        of long ago, the generations of a long time back! Are you not the one who
        cut Rahab in pieces, the one who pierced the sea-dragon? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Are you not the one who dried up the sea, the waters of the great
        deep, the one who made the depths of the sea a way for those who are redeemed
        to cross over? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So the redeemed ones of Yahweh shall return, and they shall come
        to Zion with singing, and everlasting joy shall be on their heads.  Joy and
        gladness shall appear;  sorrow and sighing shall flee away! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI, I am he who comforts you; who are you that you are afraid
        of man? He dies! And of the son of humankind? He is sacrificed as grass! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And you have forgotten Yahweh, your maker, who stretched out the
        heavens, and founded the earth. And you tremble continually, all day, because
        of the wrath of the oppressor when he takes aim to destroy. But where is
        the wrath of the oppressor? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The fettered one shall make haste to be freed. And he shall not die
        in the pit, and he shall not lack his bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For I am Yahweh, your God, who stirs up the sea, so that its waves
        roar; Yahweh of hosts is his name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I have put my words in your mouth, and I have covered you in
        the shadow of my hand, to plant the heavens and to found the earth, saying
        to Zion, \u2018You are my people.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Rouse yourself! Rouse yourself! Stand up, Jerusalem, who have drunk
        from the hand of Yahweh the cup of his wrath; you have drunk the goblet,
        the cup of staggering; you have drained it out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There is no one who guides her among all the children she has borne,
        and there is no one who grasps her by the hand among all the children she
        raised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Two things here have happened to you\u2014who will show sympathy
        for you?\u2014 devastation and destruction, famine and sword\u2014who will
        comfort you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Your children have fainted; they lie at the head of all the streets,
        like an antelope in a snare, those who are full of the wrath of Yahweh, the
        rebuke of your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore hear now this afflicted one and drunken one but not from
        wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Thus says your Lord, Yahweh, and your God pleads the cause of his
        people: \u201CLook! I have taken from your hand the cup of staggering. You
        shall not continue to drink the goblet, the cup of my wrath, any longer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And I will put it in the hand of your tormenters, who have said to
        you, \u2018Bow down that we may pass over you!\u2019 And you have made your
        back like the ground, and like the street for those who pass over you.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Yahweh Redeems Zion'
      title: Yahweh Redeems Zion
      number: 1
      content: 'Awake! Awake; put on your strength, Zion! Put on the garments of
        your beauty, Jerusalem, holy city!  For the uncircumcised and the unclean
        shall not continue to enter you any longer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Shake yourself free from the dust! Rise up; sit, Jerusalem! Free
        yourselves from the bonds of your neck, captive daughter of Zion! '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For thus says Yahweh: \u201CYou were sold for nothing, and you shall
        be redeemed without money.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says the Lord Yahweh: \u201CMy people went down to Egypt
        in the beginning, to dwell as aliens there, and Assyria oppressed him without
        cause.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And now what do I have here?\u201Ddeclares Yahweh, \u201Cfor my people
        is taken without cause. Its rulers howl,\u201D declares Yahweh\u2014\u201Cand
        my name is reviled continually, all day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore my people shall know my name, therefore in that day, that
        I am the one who speaks. Here am I.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "How delightful on the mountains are the feet of him who brings good
        news, who announces peace, who brings good news, who announces salvation,
        who says to Zion, \u201CYour God reigns as a king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The voices of your watchmen! They lift up their voices;  together
        they sing for joy; for they clearly see Yahweh\u2019s return to Zion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Break forth, sing for joy together, ruins of Jerusalem, for Yahweh
        has comforted his people; he has redeemed Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yahweh has bared his holy arm to the eyes of all the nations, and
        all the ends of the earth shall see the salvation of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Depart, depart, go out from there! You must not touch any unclean
        thing. Go out from the midst of it, keep clean, you who carry the vessels
        of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: The Servant\u2019s Suffering and Exaltation"
      title: "The Servant\u2019s Suffering and Exaltation"
      number: 12
      content: 'For you shall not go out in haste, and you shall not go in flight,
        for Yahweh is going before you, and your rear guard is the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Look, my servant shall achieve success; he shall be exalted, and
        he shall be lifted up, and he shall be very high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Just as many were appalled at you\u2014 such was his appearance beyond
        human disfigurement, and his form beyond the sons of mankind\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so he shall sprinkle many nations; because of him, kings shall shut
        their mouths.  For they shall see what has not been told them, and they shall
        consider with full attention what they have not heard. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Who has believed our message, and to whom has the arm of Yahweh
        been revealed? '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For he went up like a shoot before him, and like a root from dry
        ground. He had no form and no majesty that we should see him, and no appearance
        that we should take pleasure in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He was despised and rejected by men, a man of suffering, and acquainted
        with sickness, and like one from whom others hide their faces, he was despised,
        and we did not hold him in high regard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'However, he was the one who lifted up our sicknesses, and he carried
        our pain, yet we ourselves assumed him stricken, struck down by God and afflicted. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But he was pierced because of our transgressions, crushed because
        of our iniquities; the chastisement for our peace was upon him, and by his
        wounds we were healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All of us have wandered about like sheep; we each have turned to
        his own way; and Yahweh let fall on him the iniquity of us all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He was oppressed and afflicted, yet he did not open his mouth; he
        was brought like a lamb to the slaughter, and like a sheep is dumb before
        its shearers, so he did not open his mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He was taken by restraint of justice, and who concerned himself with
        his generation? For he was cut off from the land of the living; he received
        a blow because of the transgression of my people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He made his grave with the wicked, and with the rich in his death,
        although he had done no violence, and there was no deceit in his mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yet Yahweh was pleased to crush him; he made him sick.  If she places
        his life a guilt offering,  he will see offspring. He will prolong days,
        and the will of Yahweh will succeed in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From the trouble of his life he will see;  he will be satisfied.
        In his knowledge, the righteous one, my servant, shall declare many righteous, 
        and he is the one who will bear their iniquities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore, I will divide to him a portion among the many,  and with
        the strong ones he will divide bounty, because he poured his life out to
        death and was counted with the transgressors; and he was the one who bore
        the sin of many and will intercede for the transgressors. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fertile Wife of Yahweh'
      title: The Fertile Wife of Yahweh
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CSing for joy, barren woman; who has not borne! Burst forth
        into rejoicing and rejoice, she who has not been in labor! For the children
        of the desolate woman are more than the children of the married woman,\u201D
        says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CEnlarge the site of your tent, and let them stretch out the
        tent curtains of your dwelling place. You must not spare; make your tent
        cords long and strengthen your pegs, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'for you will spread out to the right and to the left. And your descendants
        will be heir to the nations, and they will inhabit desolate towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You must not fear, for you will not be ashamed, and you must not
        be confounded, for you will not feel abashed, for you will forget the shame
        of your youth, and you will no longer remember the disgrace of your widowhood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For your husband is your maker, his name is Yahweh of hosts; and
        your redeemer is the holy one of Israel, he is called the God of all of the
        earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For Yahweh has called you like a wife forsaken and hurt of spirit,
        like the wife of childhood when she is rejected, says your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I abandoned you for a short moment, but I will gather you with great
        compassion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I hid my face from you for a moment, in the flowing of anger, but
        I will have compassion on you with everlasting faithfulness\u201D says your
        redeemer, Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor this is like the waters of Noah to me, when I swore that
        the waters of Noah would never again pass over the earth, so I swore that
        I would not be angry at you and rebuke you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For the mountains may depart, and the hills may sway, but my faithfulness
        shall not depart from you, and my covenant of peace shall not sway,\u201D
        says Yahweh, who has compassion on you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CO afflicted one, driven away, who is not consoled. Look! I
        am about to set your stones in hard mortar, and I will lay your foundation
        with sapphires. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will make your battlements of ruby, and your gates of stones
        of beryl, and all your wall of precious stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And all your children shall be pupils of Yahweh, and the peace of
        your children shall be great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In righteousness you shall be established. Be far from oppression,
        for you shall not fear, and from terror, for it shall not come near you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If indeed one attacks, it is not from me; whoever attacks you shall
        fall because of you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Look! I myself have created the craftsman who blows the fire of coals,
        and who produces a weapon for his work; also I myself have created the destroyer
        to destroy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Every weapon formed against you shall not succeed, and you shall
        declare guilty every tongue that rises against you for judgment. This is
        the inheritance of the servants of Yahweh, and their legal right from me,\u201D
        declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Invitation to True Rewards'
      title: Invitation to True Rewards
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CHo! Everyone thirsty, come to the waters! And whoever has no
        money, come, buy and eat, and come, buy without money, wine and milk without
        price! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Why do you weigh out money for what is not food, and your labor for
        what cannot satisfy?  Listen carefully to me, and eat what is good, and let
        your soul take pleasure in rich food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Extend your ear, and come to me! Listen so that your soul may live,
        and I will make an everlasting covenant with you, the enduring proofs of
        the mercies shown to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Look! I made him a witness to the peoples, a leader and a commander
        for the peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Look! You shall call a nation that you do not know, and a nation
        that does not know you shall run to you, because of Yahweh your God, and
        the holy one of Israel, for he has glorified you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Seek Yahweh while he lets himself be found;  call him while he is
        near. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let the wicked forsake his way, and the man of sin his thoughts.
        And let him return to Yahweh, that he may take pity on him, and to our God,
        for he will forgive manifold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CFor my thoughts are not your thoughts, and your ways are not
        my ways,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor as the heavens are higher than the earth, so my ways are
        higher than your ways, and my thoughts than your thoughts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For just as the rain and the snow come down from heaven, and they
        do not return there except they have watered the earth thoroughly and cause
        it to bring forth and sprout, and give seed to the sower and bread to the
        eater, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'so shall be my word that goes out from my mouth. It shall not return
        to me without success, but shall accomplish what I desire and be successful
        in the thing for which I sent it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For you shall go out in joy, and you shall be led in peace. The mountains
        and the hills shall break forth before you, rejoicing and all the trees of
        the field shall clap hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Instead of the thorn bush, the juniper shall go up; instead of the
        brier, the myrtle shall go up, and it shall serve as a memorial to Yahweh,
        for an everlasting sign that shall not be cut off.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Salvation for All Who Obey'
      title: Salvation for All Who Obey
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CObserve justice and do righteousness, for
        my salvation is close to coming, and my justice to being revealed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Happy is the man who does this, and the son of humankind who keeps
        hold of it, who keeps the Sabbath so as not to profane it, and who keeps
        his hand from doing any evil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And do not let the foreigner who joins himself to Yahweh say, \u201CSurely
        Yahweh will separate me from his people.\u201D And do not let the eunuch
        say, \u201CLook! I am a dry tree!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For thus says Yahweh, \u201CTo the eunuchs who keep my Sabbaths,
        and choose that in which I delight, and who keep hold of my covenant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I will give them a monument and a name in my house and within
        my walls, better than sons and daughters; I will give him an everlasting
        name that shall not be cut off. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the foreigners who join themselves to Yahweh to serve him and
        to love the name of Yahweh, to become his servants, every one who keeps the
        Sabbath, so as not to profane it, and those who keep hold of my covenant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I will bring them to my holy mountain;  I will make them merry in
        my house of prayer. their burnt offerings and their sacrifices will be accepted
        on my altar, for my house shall be called a house of prayer for all peoples,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Wicked Leaders'
      title: Wicked Leaders
      number: 8
      content: 'declares the Lord Yahweh, who gathers the scattered ones of Israel
        (still I will gather to him, to his gathered ones). '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All wild animals in the field, come, to devour, all wild animals
        in the forest! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'His watchmen are blind, none of them know. They are all dumb dogs;
        they are unable to bark, panting, lying down, loving to slumber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the dogs have a greedy appetite;  they are never satisfied. 
        And they are the shepherds! They do not have understanding. They all turn
        to their own way, each one for his own gain, every one of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CCome, let me take wine, and let us carouse with intoxicating
        drink, and tomorrow will be like today, very great indeed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Idolatry is Adultery'
      title: Idolatry is Adultery
      number: 1
      content: 'The righteous one perishes, and there is no one who takes it to heart.
        And men of faithfulness are gathered, while there is no one who understands,
        for the righteous is gathered from the presence of wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'he enters into peace; they will rest on their beds, walking straight
        ahead of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CBut you, come near here, you children of a soothsayer, offspring
        of an adulterer and she who commits fornication. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'At whom do you make fun? At whom do you open your mouth and stick
        out your tongue? Are you not children of transgression, offspring of deception, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'who burn with lust among the oaks, under every leafy tree, who slaughter
        children in the valleys, under the clefts of the rocks? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your portion is among the smooth stones of the valley; they, they
        are your lot; indeed, to them you have poured out a drink offering, you have
        brought a food offering. Shall I relent concerning these things? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You have set your bed upon a high and lofty mountain; indeed, you
        went up there to slaughter sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And you have set your symbol behind the door and the doorpost; for
        you depart from me, and you go up; you make your bed wide, and you make a
        deal with them, you have loved their bed; you have seen their genitals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And you climbed down to the king with oil, and you made your perfumes
        numerous, and you sent your envoys far away,  and you sent down deep to Sheol. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You grow weary by the greatness of your way, but you did not say,
        \u2018Despairing!\u2019 You found the renewal of your strength,  therefore
        you do not grow weak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And of whom were you afraid and feared, that you deceived and did
        not remember me? Did you not place it on your heart? Have I not been silent,
        even from long ago, and so you do not fear me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I myself will declare your righteousness and your works, but they
        will not benefit you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Peace for the Contrite'
      title: Peace for the Contrite
      number: 13
      content: "When you cry, let your collection deliver you, and the wind will
        carry all of them away; a breath will take them away. But he who takes refuge
        in me shall take possession of the land, and he shall inherit my holy mountain.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And one shall say, \u201CBuild up, build up! Clear the way! Remove
        the obstacles from the way of my people!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For thus says the high and lofty one who resides forever, and whose
        name is holy: \u201CI reside in a high and holy place, and with the contrite
        and humble of spirit, to revive the spirit of the humble, and to revive the
        heart of the contrite.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For I will not attack forever, and I will not be angry forever, for
        the spirit will grow faint before me, and the breaths that I myself I have
        made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I was angry because of his sin of gain, and I struck him; I hid and
        I was angry, but he walked apostate, in the ways of his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I have seen his ways, but I will heal him; and I will lead him and
        give him and his mourners comfort as a recompense, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "creating fruit of lips. Peace, peace to the far and near,\u201D says
        Yahweh, \u201Cand I will heal him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But the wicked are like the churning sea, that is not able to keep
        quiet, and its waters toss up mire and mud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "There is no peace,\u201D says my God, \u201Cfor the wicked.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: True Fasts and Sabbaths'
      title: True Fasts and Sabbaths
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CCall with the throat; you must not keep back! lift up your
        voice like a trumpet, and declare to my people their rebellion, and to the
        house of Jacob their sins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yet they seek me day by day, and they desire the knowledge of my
        ways like a nation that practiced righteousness, and had not forsaken the
        judgment of its God; they ask me for righteous judgments,  they desire the
        closeness of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Why do we fast, and you do not see it? We humiliate our soul,
        and you do not notice it?\u2019 Look! You find delight on the day of your
        fast, and you oppress all your workers! "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Look! You fast to quarrel and strife, and to strike with a wicked
        fist.  You shall not fast as you do today,  to make your voice heard on the
        height. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Is the fast I choose like this, a day for humankind to humiliate
        himself? To bow his head like a reed, and make his bed on sackcloth and ashes;
        you call this a fast and a day of pleasure to Yahweh? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Is this not the fast I choose: to release the bonds of injustice,
        to untie the ropes of the yoke, and to let the oppressed go free, and tear
        every yoke to pieces? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Is it not to break your bread for the hungry? You must bring home
        the poor, the homeless. When you see the naked, you must cover him, and you
        must not hide yourself from your relatives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then your light shall break forth like the dawn, and your healing
        shall grow quickly. And your salvation shall go before you; the glory of
        Yahweh will be your rear guard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then you shall call, and Yahweh himself will answer. You shall cry
        for help, and he will say, \u2018Here I am!\u2019 If you remove from among
        you the yoke, the finger-pointing and evil speech,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'if you offer your soul to the hungry, and you satisfy the appetite
        of the afflicted, then your light shall rise in the darkness, and your darkness
        will be like noon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Yahweh will lead you continually, and satisfy your soul in a
        barren land, and he will strengthen your bones, and you shall be like a well-watered
        garden, and like a spring of water whose water does not fail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they shall rebuild ancient ruins from you; you shall erect the
        foundations of many generations,  and you shall be called the bricklayer
        of the breach, the restorer of paths to live in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If you hold your foot back from the Sabbath, from doing your affairs
        on my holy day,  if you call the Sabbath a pleasure, the holy day of Yahweh
        honorable, if you honor him more than doing your ways, than finding your
        affairs and speaking a word, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "then you shall take your pleasure in Yahweh, and I will make you
        ride upon the heights of the earth, and I will feed you the heritage of Jacob
        your ancestor,  for the mouth of Yahweh has spoken.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rampant Transgression'
      title: Rampant Transgression
      number: 1
      content: 'Look! The hand of Yahweh is not too short to save,  and his ear is
        not too dull to hear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Rather, your iniquities have been barriers between you and your God,
        and your sins have hidden his face from you, from hearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For your hands are defiled with blood, and your fingers with iniquity.
        Your lips have spoken lies, your tongue speaks wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'There is nobody who pleads with justice, and there is nobody who
        judges with honesty. They rely on nothing and speak vanity. They conceive
        trouble and beget iniquity; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'they hatch viper eggs, and they weave a spider web. One who eats
        their eggs dies, and that which is pressed is hatched as a serpent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Their webs cannot become clothing, and they cannot cover themselves
        with their works. Their works are works of iniquity, and deeds of violence
        are in their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Their feet run to evil, and they hasten to shed innocent blood. Their
        thoughts are thoughts of iniquity; devastation and destruction are in their
        highways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They do not know the way of peace, and there is no justice in their
        firm paths. They have made their paths crooked for themselves; everyone who
        walks in it knows no peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore justice is far from us, and righteousness does not reach
        us. We wait for light, but look! there is darkness; for brightness, but we
        walk in darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We grope like the blind along a wall, and we grope as without eyes.
        We stumble at noon as in the twilight; among the strong we are like the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'We all groan like bears, and we coo mutteringly like doves. We wait
        for justice, but there is none; for salvation, but it is far from us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For our transgressions are numerous before you, and our sins testify
        against us. Indeed, our transgressions are with us, and we know our iniquities: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'transgressing and denying Yahweh, and turning away from following
        our God; speaking oppression and falsehood, conceiving and uttering words
        of deception from the heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And justice is pushed back, and righteousness stands afar; for truth
        stumbles in the public square, and straightforwardness is unable to enter, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and truth is missing, and he who turns aside from evil is plundered.
        And Yahweh saw, and it was displeasing in his eyes that there was no justice '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he saw that there was no man, and he was appalled that there
        was no one who intercedes, so his arm came to assist him, and his righteousness
        was what sustained him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he put on righteousness like a breastplate, and a helmet of salvation
        on his head, and he put on garments of vengeance for clothing, and he wrapped
        himself in zeal as in a robe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'According to deeds, so he will repay; wrath to his enemies, requital
        to those who are his enemies.  He will repay requital to the coastlands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So they shall fear the name of Yahweh from the west, and his glory
        from the sunrise, for he will come like a narrow stream; the wind of Yahweh
        drives it on. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAnd a redeemer will come to Zion, to those in Jacob who turn
        away from transgression,\u201D declares Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAnd as for me, this is my covenant with them, says Yahweh:
        my spirit that is upon you, and my words that I have placed in your mouth
        shall not depart from your mouth, or from the mouths of your children,  or
        from the mouths of your children\u2019s children,\u201D  says Yahweh, \u201Cfrom
        now on and forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zion Glorified'
      title: Zion Glorified
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CArise, shine! For your light has come, and the glory of Yahweh
        has risen on you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For look! darkness shall cover the earth, and thick darkness the
        peoples, but Yahweh will rise on you, and his glory will appear over you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And nations shall come to your light, and kings to the bright light
        of your sunrise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Lift up your eyes all around and see! All of them gather; they come
        to you. Your sons shall come from afar, and your daughters shall be looked
        after on the hip. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then you shall see and you shall be radiant; and your heart shall
        tremble and open itself wide, because the abundance of the sea shall fall
        upon you; the wealth of the nations shall come to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A multitude of camels shall cover you, the young male camels of Midian
        and Ephah. All those from Sheba shall come; they shall bring gold and frankincense,
        and they shall proclaim the praise of Yahweh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the flocks of Kedar shall be gathered to you; the rams of Nebaioth
        shall serve you. They shall present a sacrifice for favor on my altar, and
        I will glorify my honorable house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who are these? They fly like a cloud, and like doves to their coops. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Because the coastlands wait for me, and the ships of Tarshish are
        first to bring your children from afar, their silver and gold with them,
        for the name of Yahweh your God, and for the holy one of Israel, because
        he has glorified you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And foreigners shall build your walls, and their kings shall serve
        you, for in my anger I struck you, but in my favor I have taken pity on you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And your gates shall continually be open, day and night they shall
        not be shut, to bring you the wealth of nations, and their kings shall be
        led. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the nation and the kingdom that will not serve you shall perish,
        and the nations shall be utterly devastated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The glory of Lebanon shall come to you; the cypress, the plane, and
        the pine together, to glorify the place of my sanctuary, and I will do honor
        to the place of my feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the children of those who oppressed you shall come to you bending
        low, and all those who treated you disrespectfully shall bow down at the
        soles of your feet. And they shall call you the city of Yahweh, Zion of the
        holy one of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Instead of you being forsaken and hated with no one passing through, 
        I will make you an everlasting object of pride,  a joy of coming generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And you shall suck the milk of nations, and suck the breast of kings,
        and you shall know that I am Yahweh your Savior, and your Redeemer, the Strong
        One of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Instead of bronze I will bring gold, and instead of iron I will bring
        silver, and instead of wood, bronze, and instead of stones, iron. And I will
        appoint peace as your overseer, and righteousness as your ruling body.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Violence shall no longer be heard in your land; devastation or destruction
        on your borders. And you shall call your walls Salvation, and your gates,
        Praise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sun shall no longer be your light by day, and for bright light
        the moon shall not give you light, but Yahweh will be your everlasting light,
        and your God your glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Your sun shall no longer go down, and your moon shall not wane, 
        for Yahweh himself will be your everlasting light, and your days of mourning
        shall come to an end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And all your people shall be righteous; they shall take possession
        of the land forever, the shoot of his planting, the work of my hands, to
        show my glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The small one shall become a tribe, and the smallest one a mighty
        nation. I am Yahweh; I will hasten it in its time.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Year of Yahweh\u2019s Favor"
      title: "The Year of Yahweh\u2019s Favor"
      number: 1
      content: 'The Spirit of the Lord Yahweh is upon me, because Yahweh has anointed
        me, he has sent me to bring good news to the oppressed, to bind up the brokenhearted, 
        to proclaim release to the captives and liberation to those who are bound, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "to proclaim the year of Yahweh\u2019s favor, and our God\u2019s day
        of vengeance, to comfort all those in mourning, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'to give for those in mourning in Zion, to give them a head wrap instead
        of ashes, the oil of joy instead of mourning, a garment of praise instead
        of a faint spirit. And they will be called oaks of righteousness, the planting
        of Yahweh, to show his glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they shall build the ancient ruins, they shall erect the former
        deserted places. And they shall restore the devastated cities,  the deserted
        places of many generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And strangers shall stand and feed your flocks,  and foreigners shall
        be your farmers and vinedressers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But you shall be called the priests of Yahweh, you will be called
        servers of our God. You shall eat the wealth of the nations, and you shall
        boast in their riches. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Instead of your shame, a double portion, and instead of insult, they
        will rejoice over their portion. Therefore they will take a double portion
        in their land; they shall possess everlasting joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For I, Yahweh, love justice, hate robbery and injustice, and I will
        faithfully give their reward, and I will make an everlasting covenant with
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And their descendants will be known among the nations, and their
        offspring in the midst of the peoples. All those who see them shall recognize
        them, that they are descendants whom Yahweh has blessed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will rejoice greatly in Yahweh; my being shall shout in exultation
        in my God. For he has clothed me with garments of salvation, he has covered
        me with the robe of righteousness, as a bridegroom adorns himself with a
        head wrap like a priest, and as a bride adorns herself with her jewelry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For as the earth produces its sprout, and as a garden makes its plants
        sprout, so the Lord Yahweh will make righteousness sprout, and praise before
        all the nations. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zion\u2019s New Identity"
      title: "Zion\u2019s New Identity"
      number: 1
      content: 'For the sake of Zion I will not be silent, and for the sake of Jerusalem
        I will not maintain a quiet attitude, until her righteousness goes out like
        the bright light, and her salvation burns like a torch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the nations shall see your righteousness, and all the kings your
        glory, and you will be called a new name that the mouth of Yahweh will designate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you shall be a crown of beauty in the hand of Yahweh, and a headband
        of royalty in the hand of your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It shall no longer be said of you, \u201CForsaken,\u201D and it shall
        no longer be said of your land, \u201CDesolation!\u201D but you will be called
        \u201CMy Delight Is In Her,\u201D and your land, \u201CMarried,\u201D for
        Yahweh delights in you, and your land shall be married. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For as a young man marries a virgin, so shall your sons marry you,
        and as is the joy of the bridegroom over the bride, so shall your God rejoice
        over you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I have appointed watchmen upon your walls, Jerusalem; all day and
        all night they shall never be silent. You who profess Yahweh have no rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And you must not give him rest until he establishes, and until he
        makes Jerusalem an object of praise in the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Yahweh has sworn by his right hand, and by his mighty arm,  \u201CSurely
        I will never again give your grain as food to your enemies,  and surely foreigners
        shall not drink your new wine at which you have labored.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But those who gather it shall eat it, and they shall praise Yahweh,
        and those who gather it shall drink it in my holy courts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Pass through, pass through the gates! Make the way clear for the
        people! Pile up, pile up the highway; clear it of stones!  Lift up an ensign
        over the peoples! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Look! Yahweh has proclaimed to the end of the earth: Say to daughter
        Zion, \u201CLook, your salvation is coming! Look, his reward is with him,
        and his reward before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they shall call them \u201CThe Holy People, The Redeemed Of Yahweh,\u201D
        and you shall be called \u201CSought After, A City Is Not Forsaken.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Yahweh\u2019s Day of Vengeance"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Day of Vengeance"
      number: 1
      content: "Who is this, coming from Edom, from Bozrah in bright red garments?
        Who is this honored in his garment, lying down in his great strength? \u201CIt
        is I, speaking in justice, mighty to save!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Why are your garments red, and your garments like he who treads in
        the winepress? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI have trodden the winepress alone, and there was no man from
        the peoples with me. And I trod them in my anger, and I trampled them in
        my wrath, and spattered their juice on my garments, and stained all my clothing, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for the day of vengeance was in my heart, and the year of my blood-vengeance
        has come! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I looked, but there was no helper, and I was appalled, but there
        was no one who sustains, so my arm came to assist me, and my wrath was what
        sustained me. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Remembering Yahweh\u2019s Mercy"
      title: "Remembering Yahweh\u2019s Mercy"
      number: 6
      content: "And I trampled peoples in my anger, and I made them drunk in my wrath,
        and I brought their juice down to the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will mention the loyal love of Yahweh, the praises of Yahweh, according
        to all that Yahweh has done for us, and the greatness of goodness to the
        house of Israel that he has done to them according to his mercy and the abundance
        of his loyal love. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said, \u201CSurely my people are children; they will not break
        faith.\u201D And he became a Savior to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In all their distress, there was no distress,  and the messenger
        of his presence saved them, in his love and compassion he himself redeemed
        them, and he lifted them up, and he supported them all the days of old. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But they were the ones who rebelled, and they grieved his Holy Spirit, 
        so he became an enemy to them;  he himself fought against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then his people remembered the days of old, of Moses. Where is the
        one who led up them from the sea with the shepherds of his flock? Where is
        the one who puts his Holy Spirit inside him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'who made his magnificent arm move at the right hand of Moses, who
        divided the waters before them,  to make an everlasting name for himself, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'who led them through the depths? They did not stumble like a horse
        in the desert; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Prayer for Mercy'
      title: Prayer for Mercy
      number: 14
      content: 'like cattle in the valley that goes down, the Spirit of Yahweh gave
        him rest,  so you lead your people to make a magnificent name for yourself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Look from heaven, and see from the lofty residence of your holiness
        and glory. Where are your zeal and strength? Your compassion and mercy to
        me hold themselves back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For you are our father, although Abraham does not know us, and Israel
        does not acknowledge us. You, Yahweh are our father, Our Redeemer from of
        old is your name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Why do you make us wander, Yahweh? You harden our heart from your
        ways so that we do not fear you. Turn back for the sake of your servants,
        the tribes of your inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Your holy people took possession for a little while; our adversaries
        have trampled down your sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'We have been since antiquity; you did not rule them; they were not
        called by your name.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '   Would that you would tear the heavens and come down; the mountains
        would quake before you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: ' as fire kindles brushwood, the fire causes water to boil, to make
        your name known to your adversaries, that the nations might tremble from
        your presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When you did terrible deeds which we did not expect, you came down;
        the mountains quaked because of your presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And since ancient times they have not heard, have not listened, no
        eye has seen a God except you; he acts for the one who waits for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You meet with the one who rejoices, one who does righteousness. In
        your ways they remember you. Look! You were angry and we sinned against them
        in ancient times and we were saved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And we all have become like the unclean, and all our deeds of justice
        like a menstrual cloth, And we all wither like a leaf, and our iniquities
        take us away like the wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And there is no one who calls on your name, who pulls himself up
        to keep hold of you, for you have hidden your face from us,  and melted us
        into the hand of our iniquity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Yet now Yahweh, you are our father; we are the clay and you are our
        potter,  and we all are the work of your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You must not be exceedingly angry, Yahweh, and you must not remember
        iniquity forever! Look! Behold, now! We all are your people! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Your holy cities have become a wilderness; Zion has become a wilderness,
        Jerusalem a desolation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Our holy and beautiful temple, where our ancestors praised you has
        been burned by fire, and all our precious objects have become ruins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Will you control yourself because of these, Yahweh? Will you be silent?
        And will you oppress us exceedingly? '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment and Salvation'
      title: Judgment and Salvation
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CI let myself be sought by those who did not ask; I let myself
        be found by those who did not seek me. I said, \u2018Here I am; here I am!\u2019
        to a nation that did not call on my name; "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I spread out my hands all day to a stubborn people, those who walk
        after their thoughts in the way that is not good, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the people who provoke me to anger continually to my face, slaughtering
        for sacrifices in the garden, and making smoke offerings on bricks, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'who sit in graves and spend the night in secret places,  who eat
        the flesh of swine with a fragment of impurity in their vessels, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "who say, \u201CKeep to yourself!  You must not come near me, for
        I am too holy for you!\u201D These are a smoke in my nostrils,  a fire burning
        all day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Look! It is written before me: I will not be silent, but I will repay;
        and I will repay in the fold of their garment '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "your iniquities and the iniquities of your ancestors together, says
        Yahweh, because they made smoke offerings on the mountains and they taunted
        me on the hills, I will measure their punishment from the beginning into
        the fold of their garment.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CJust as the new wine is found in the cluster,
        and they say \u2018You must not destroy it, for there is a blessing in it,\u2019
        so I will do for the sake of my servants by not destroying everyone.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And I will bring descendant s out from Jacob, and a people from Judah
        to take possession of my mountain, and my chosen ones shall inherit it, and
        my servants shall settle there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Sharon shall become a pasture for flocks,  and the valley of
        Achor a resting place for herds  for my people who have sought me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But you who forsake Yahweh, forgetting my holy mountain,  who set
        a table for Fortune, and who pour out a jug of mixed wine for Destiny, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and I will remit you to the sword, and all of you shall bow down
        to the slaughter, because I called, but you did not answer; I spoke, but
        you did not listen, but you did the evil in my eyes, and you chose that in
        which I do not delight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore thus says the Lord Yahweh: \u201CLook! My servants shall
        eat but you, you shall be hungry. Look! My servants shall drink but you,
        you shall be thirsty. Look! My servants shall rejoice but you, you shall
        be ashamed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Look! My servants shall shout for joy, but you, you shall cry out
        for pain and howl for sadness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And you shall leave your name to my chosen ones as a curse, and the
        Lord Yahweh will kill you, and he will give his servants another name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: New Creation'
      title: New Creation
      number: 16
      content: 'Whoever blesses himself in the land shall bless himself by the God
        of trustworthiness, and the one who swears an oath in the land shall swear
        by the God of trustworthiness, because the former troubles are forgotten,
        and they are hidden from my eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For look! I am about to create new heavens and a new earth, and the
        former things shall not be remembered, and they shall not come to mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But rejoice and shout in exultation forever and ever over what I
        am about to create! For look! I am about to create Jerusalem as a source
        of rejoicing, and her people as a source of joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will shout in exultation over Jerusalem, and I will rejoice
        over my people, and the sound of weeping shall no longer be heard in it,
        or the sound of a cry for help. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'There will no longer be a nursing infant who lives only a few days,
        or an old man who does not fill his days, for the boy will die a hundred
        years old,  and the one who fails to reach a hundred years will be considered
        accursed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they shall build houses and inhabit them, and they shall plant
        vineyards and eat their fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They shall not build and another inhabit; they shall not plant and
        another eat. For the days of my people shall be like the days of a tree,
        and my chosen ones shall enjoy the work of their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They shall not labor for nothing, and they shall not give birth to
        horror, for they shall be offspring blessed by Yahweh, and their descendants
        with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And this will happen: before they call, I myself will answer; while
        still they are speaking, I myself will hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The wolf and the lamb shall feed like one, and the lion shall eat
        straw like the ox, but dust shall be the serpent\u2019s food. They shall
        do no evil, and they shall not destroy on all my holy mountain,\u201D says
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Proper Worship'
      title: Proper Worship
      number: 1
      content: "Thus says Yahweh: \u201CHeaven is my throne, and the earth is the
        footstool for my feet. Where is this house that you would build for me? And
        where is this resting place for me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And my hand has made all these things, and all these came to be,\u201D 
        declares Yahweh, \u201Cbut I look to this one: to the humble and the contrite
        of spirit and the one frightened at my word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The one who slaughters a bull strikes a man; the one who slaughters
        a lamb for sacrifice breaks the neck of a dog. The one who offers an offering,
        the blood of swine; the one who offers frankincense blesses an idol. Indeed,
        they themselves have chosen their ways, and their soul delights in their
        abhorrence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Indeed, I myself I will choose their ill treatment, and I will bring
        them objects of their dread, because I called, and no one answered;  I spoke
        and they did not listen, but they did the evil in my eyes, and they chose
        that in which I do not delight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Hear the word of Yahweh, you who are frightened at his word: Your
        brothers who hate you, who exclude you for my name\u2019s sake have said,
        \u201CLet Yahweh be honored so that we may see your joy!\u201D But they themselves
        shall be ashamed. "
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Zion\u2019s Delivery"
      title: "Zion\u2019s Delivery"
      number: 6
      content: 'A voice, an uproar from the city! A voice from the temple! The voice
        of Yahweh paying back his enemies! '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Before she was in labor she gave birth; before labor pains came to
        her, she gave birth to a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who has heard anything like this? Who has seen anything like these
        things? Can a land be born in one day? Or can a nation be born in a moment?
        Yet when she was in labor, Zion indeed gave birth to her children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shall I myself I break open and not deliver?\u201D says Yahweh, \u201Cor
        I who delivers lock up the womb?\u201D says your God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CRejoice with Jerusalem and shout in exultation with her, all
        those who love her! Rejoice with her in joy, all those who mourn over her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "so that you may suck and be satisfied from her consoling breast, 
        so that you may drink deeply and refresh yourselves from her heavy breast.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For thus says Yahweh: \u201CLook! I am about to spread prosperity
        out to her like a river, and the wealth of the nations like an overflowing
        stream, and you shall suck and be carried on the hip; and you shall you shall
        be played with on the knees. "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Yahweh\u2019s Final Judgment"
      title: "Yahweh\u2019s Final Judgment"
      number: 13
      content: 'As a man whose mother comforts him, so I myself will comfort you,
        and you shall be comforted in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And you shall see and your heart shall rejoice, and your bones shall
        flourish like the grass, and the hand of Yahweh shall make itself known to
        his servants, and he shall curse his enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For look! Yahweh will come in fire, and his chariots like the storm
        wind, to give back his anger in wrath, and his rebuke in flames of fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For Yahweh enters into judgment on all flesh with fire and his sword,
        and those slain by Yahweh shall be many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Those who sanctify themselves and those who cleanse themselves to
        go into the gardens after the one in the middle, eating the flesh of swine
        and detestable things and rodents together shall come to an end!\u201D declares
        Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAnd I\u2014their works and thoughts!\u2014am about to come
        to gather all nations and tongues, and they shall come and see my glory. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will set a sign among them, and I will send survivors from
        them to the nations: Tarshish, Pul, and Lud, who draw the bow; Tubal and
        Javan, the faraway coastlands that have not heard of my fame, and have not
        seen my glory. And they shall declare my glory among the nations, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and bring all your countrymen from all the nations as an offering
        to Yahweh on horses and chariots and in litters and on mules and camels,
        to my holy mountain, Jerusalem,\u201D says Yahweh, \u201Cjust as the sons
        of Israel bring an offering in a clean vessel to the house of Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And indeed, I will take some of them as priests and the Levites,\u201D
        says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor just as the new heavens and earth that I am about to make
        shall stand before me,\u201D declares Yahweh, \u201Cso shall your descendants
        and your name stand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And this shall happen: From new moon to new moon and from Sabbath
        to Sabbath all flesh shall come to bow in worship before me,\u201D says Yahweh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAnd they shall go out and look at the corpses of the people
        who have rebelled against me, for their worm shall not die, and their fire
        shall not be quenched, and they shall be an abhorrence to all flesh.\u201D "
      comments: []
